title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in square baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and beaten egg.
Put mixture over fruit.
Drizzle melted butter over this. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Beat oleo, sugar and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat all ingredients together.
Pour half of batter in tube pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon. Sprinkle 1/2 over cake batter.
Spoon in rest of cake batter and sprinkle rest of sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: copper carrot salad
directions: Boil sliced carrots in salt water 10 minutes.
Mix next six ingredients well and pour over drained carrots.
Add peppers and onions.
Mix well and marinate in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: pasta bagna cauda
directions: Heat
oil and butter in a small pan over very low heat.
In another small pan (preferably nonstick), cook garlic in a bit of oil until soft.
Add anchovies and cook until a paste is formed, stirring occasionally (about 4 to 5 minutes).
Add fish/garlic mixture to the oil/butter mixture and stir well.
Cook pasta al dente and toss with sauce.
Blend in the whipped egg.
Add cheese and pepper to taste.
Excellent as small meal or appetizer/first course for grilled meat or beef brochette.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Add enough water to cover; cook on medium for 20 minutes.
Add onions, potatoes, carrots, salt and pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to thicken (more or less flour may be added).

title: 7-up salad
directions: Empty lime jello, Philadelphia cream cheese and 1 cup boiling water in large mixing bowl.
With hand mixer, beat mixture until cream cheese dissolves.
Add 7-Up, pineapple and nuts.
Stir well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and place in refrigerator until firm.
Can be eaten as salad or dessert.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain all of canned vegetables.
Mix other ingredients and fold into vegetables.
Place in casserole and cover with Pepperidge Farm seasoned bread crumbs covered with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(May be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated until baking.)

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Pare asparagus if needed and trim off tough ends.
Wash asparagus, then place in saucepan with salted boiling water.
Drop in 1/2 lemon and cook 12 to 18 minutes, depending on size.
Do not overcook.
Test if asparagus are cooked by prickling with sharp knife.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Drain asparagus well.
Place in buttered baking dish and cover with cheese sauce.
Top with grated Gruyere cheese.
Brown in oven 12 minutes.
Serve.

title: mock sausage
directions: Wash dried beans, cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain. Cook in salted boiling water until tender, about 1 hour.
Drain and press through a strainer.
Add 2 beaten eggs, seasoning, salt and pepper.
Form into patties.
Roll in crumbs, then in 1 beaten egg, then in crumbs again.
Saute in hot oil until brown.
Good with tomato sauce.

title: cajun special
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients except rice and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook rice.
Serve beans and sausage mixture over rice.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine onions, celery, basil, garlic and thyme in separate bowl; set aside.
In 3-gallon saucepot, brown bacon, then add clams and juice.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add onions, celery, basil, garlic, thyme, pepper and oregano.
Simmer until celery is done.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Combine shortening, eggs, orange juice, water and cherries.
Mix well.
Add to dry ingredients and blend until moistened.
Place in a greased loaf pan, 9 x 4 x 3-inch.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Chill dough.
Maybe add more flour when you roll out dough. Cut out.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Does not take long.

title: lemon cheese cake(no bake easy)
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until smooth; gradually add 1/2 cup of milk and beat until smooth.
Add remaining milk and instant pudding.
Beat well.
Pour into cooled graham cracker crust.
For extra lemon flavor, add a few drops of lemon juice.

title: little inn sunday brunch
directions: In a microsafe bowl, melt the butter on Medium-high power for 10 seconds.
Add the onion.
Microwave on High power for 2 to 3 minutes, until soft.
Add ham and chopped chilies.
Slice the crust off the bread, if desired.
Cut slices into triangles. Place half of them in individual microsafe serving dishes.
Top with ham-onion mixture.
Sprinkle with most of the cheese.
Top with remaining bread.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook well until all vegetables are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and white membrane.
Crumble beef into 1 1/2-quart microwaveproof dish.
Add onion.
Cook in High for about 5 minutes, stirring once during cooking.
Cook until meat loses its red color.
Drain.
Stir in salt, pepper, rice and half of tomato sauce.
Place in microwaveproof baking dish.
Top each pepper with remaining tomato sauce.
Cover with waxed paper and cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes, or just until peppers are tender.

title: fruit cole slaw
directions: In large bowl, toss cabbage and grapes together.
In small bowl, mix sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Pour over cabbage and toss until cabbage is completely covered with sauce.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix together.
Press in a
9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Put in refrigerator.
Must be cool before next layer.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Heat tomatoes and margarine in saucepan until margarine melts. Mix in bread, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered baking dish and sprinkle with allspice.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Combine
sugar,
shortening
and
molasses.
Beat until smooth.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, ginger, vanilla and salt. Beat well.	Add
flour,
1 cup at a time.
Blend well.
Divide into 6 parts.
Pat into greased cake pans with a floured hand. Bake layers
at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes or until light brown. When cool, spread 2/3 cup of apple mixture between layers.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet and drain.
Add all ingredients; stir well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer for 1 hour or until ready to serve, stirring occasionally.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Line baking dish with aluminum foil, leaving enough foil to cover pork chops and potatoes.
Place pork chops on one end of dish, carrots and onion on other end.
Dot potato-carrot mixture with butter.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are soft and pork chops are done.
Cover entire dish with cream of mushroom soup.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add dry ingredients and milk to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and stir.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: florida wild plum jelly
directions: Bill and I found that substituting 1 1/2 cups frozen apple juice for 1 1/2 cups plum juice made less tart jelly.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs until thick; add sugar gradually.
Beat, then add oil, cocoa and remaining ingredients; beat.
Grease and flour pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar and cocoa. Stir in butter, milk and corn syrup. Bring to boil. Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Take from heat. Add immediately the sifted confectioners sugar, vanilla and nuts. Stir until sugar is completely blended. Turn into 8-inch square pan and pat out with fingers. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: rice for fried chicken
directions: Melt the margarine in pan. Add the rice and chicken noodle soup. Stir over medium heat until golden brown. Add the water. Cover and simmer until done, checking to see if needs water.

title: no guilt brownies(100 calories each if cut in 16 pieces.)
directions: Melt chocolate.
Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar. Bake in 8-inch square pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until just set.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into 16 pieces.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cut up the potatoes and onions. Cook in 3 cups water.
Pour mixture into blender in thirds.
Blend thoroughly, adding bouillon cubes.
Do not drain water.
Leave some chunks in the potatoes. Pour mixture into large pot and add butter, half and half, milk, salt and pepper. Simmer until warm.
Do not boil.
Top with grated cheese.

title: peach aspic with cream cheese dressing
directions: In a bowl, combine gelatin and water.
Stir until dissolved. Stir in orange juice, peel, lemon juice, 1 1/2 cups peaches and sugar.
Pour into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: tourtiere pie
directions: Brown ground pork in skillet; drain off excess fat.
Stir in water, onion, bread crumbs, salt, sage, pepper, and nutmeg. Simmer, covered until onion is tender, about 20 minutes, stirring often.
Line 9 inch pie plate with pastry; fill with meat mixture. Adjust top crust, seal and flute edges.
Cut slits in top.

title: chili verde
directions: Saute onions.
When translucent, add cubed meat.
Cook for a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Add jar or can of salsa, garbanzo beans and all seasonings.
Stir.
Cover and let simmer very slowly for approximately 20 minutes.
Add bag of chips.
(The chips thicken the chili and provide salt.)
Finish cooking for another 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.
Cooking time is 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1 cup milk.
Mixture should be loose, but not runny.
Add more milk, if needed.
Form into any shape and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix first four ingredients. Mix remaining ingredients and blend in food processor.
Freeze in ice cube trays or molds. After frozen, store in plastic bags.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, cream and sugar in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in thawed whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: brian's beef stroganoff
directions: To cook by microwave:
Heat butter in glass bowl on High for 2 minutes. Add onion to butter.
Cook on High for 2.5 minutes.
Stir once.
Add beef, mushrooms and garlic powder.
Cook on Medium-High for 7 minutes.
Stir twice.
Drain and reserve liquid; add enough broth, if needed, to reserve liquid to equal 3/4 cup.
Sprinkle beef with salt, pepper and flour.
Mix together until flour thickens with beef.
Add the liquid back into beef and stir together.
Cook on High for 3 minutes or until sauce is thickened. Stir in sour cream.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Instead of the alcohol	you may substitute a mixture of 1 teaspoon sugar to 4 tablespoons black coffee.

title: bevo mill's cheddar cheese and chive biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add butter and oil while mixing until all oils are mixed in.
Add milk and knead just until mix pulls away from side of bowl.
Don't overmix.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet from a large spoon.
Each biscuit should weigh about 2 ounces.
Bake in 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: leftover roast beef special
directions: Cut leftover roast in bite-size pieces.
Mix with the three cans of soup and mushrooms.
Cook noodles according to package directions and add to beef and soup mix.
Add beef broth if beef and noodle mixture seems a little dry.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta ala carbonara
directions: Cook bacon, but do not get too crisp.
Drain on paper toweling to remove as much grease as possible.
In a large skillet, pour enough olive oil to cover bottom of pan.
Add the onion and cook over medium heat until soft, but do not burn.
Add more oil if necessary.
Drain on paper towel to remove as much grease as possible.
In the same pan, cook the mushrooms until almost soft in a little butter.
Do not overcook.
Add the onions and bacon to this pan.
Mix well and reduce heat to low.

title: can't stop eating them pretzels
directions: Combine in a microwave safe bowl, the buttery oil, dry ranch dressing, dill weed and garlic powder.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in pineapple; sift flour, soda, salt and nutmeg and add with chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sunset's christmas fruitcake
directions: In a
large
bowl,
combine fruits, nuts, orange juice, honey, 2	tablespoons
orange
liqueur and spices; set aside. With electric mixer, beat together butter and sugar until well blended; then
beat
in
eggs,
one at a time.
Stir together flour
and soda.
Stir
flour mixture into creamed mixture by hand.
Add fruit
mixture
and
stir
until well distributed. Evenly
spoon batter
into
2 well greased 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch loaf pans.	Bake at	300° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.
Cool in pan
for
10 minutes,
remove from pans then cool completely. Wrap cakes in double thickness of cheesecloth saturated with 2 tablespoons orange
liqueur.
Overwrap	in
foil.
Store
in refrigerator for 2 weeks before sampling.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli, cauliflower and onion. Add cheese and bacon bits. Mix sugar, salad dressing, vinegar in small bowl. Pour over broccoli mixture and toss well.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Grease stick pan.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg well.
Add Sweet 'N Low to mayonnaise; mix well.
Alternately add meal and milk until a thin batter is formed.
Pour into greased stick pan. Bake until golden brown, approximately 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 7 corn sticks.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute butter, baco chips and onion until soft.
Add corn and heat.
Add milk, potatoes, salt and other spices.
Add the cheese. Heat until cheese is melted.
Do not boil.

title: quick cream cheese danish
directions: Press 1 can crescent rolls in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan, pinching together seams.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and lemon juice together.
Spread on top of rolls.

title: eggplant and green peppers sauteed with miso(mmm, it's good)
directions: Very, very popular; we always eat egg roll in morning with breakfast.
Rice, egg roll, miso soup, fish and dried seaweed is the favorite breakfast in Japan.

title: fried vegetables
directions: Mix all together; pour 1 1/2 cups of flour or meal over them. Fry in a skillet with oil until tender.

title: almost eskimo ice cream
directions: Mix fruit with cream cheese.
Fold in whipped topping.
Serve in ice cream cones.
Can be served immediately or frozen slightly in cones.
Will freeze hard!

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, melted butter, seasonings and beaten eggs. Arrange mixture alternately in layers with buttered bread and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken easy
directions: Place
chicken
in
casserole dish and pour ingredients over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: fruited pork
directions: In a 2-quart covered casserole, mix water, vinegar, molasses, soy sauce and pepper.
Microwave at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until hot, stirring after half the time.
Stir in pork.
Cover; marinate at room temperature for about 1 hour.
Drain pork, reserving 2 tablespoons marinade.
Set aside reserved marinade. Place casserole with pork on Micro-Go-Round in microwave oven. Microwave at 70% (Medium-high) for 3 to 6 minutes, or until pork is no longer pink.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add apples, walnuts and raisins.
Microwave at 70% (Medium-high) for 2 to 3 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Stir in oranges; cover and set aside.
In small mixing bowl, blend reserved marinade, reserved cooking liquid and Mandarin orange juice.
Add cornstarch; mix well.
Microwave at High for 2 to 3 minutes, or until thickened, stirring 3 or 4 times. Stir into pork mixture.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dieter's potato salad
directions: Lightly toss all ingredients and chill.
Surprisingly tasty and satisfying.
Serves 2.

title: popeye pot pie
directions: Wash fresh spinach and discard stems.
Steam in a covered sauce pan over low heat until the leaves are wilted.
Drain in a colander or sieve, press out liquid and chop spinach.
(Or thaw frozen chopped spinach and press out liquid.)
Mix remaining ingredients together, then fold in spinach.
Pour mixture into a well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Cut into 6 wedges and serve warm.

title: all day apple butter
directions: Place apples in slow cooker. Combine sugar, cinnamon, cloves and salt. Pour over apples and mix well. Cover and cook on high 1 hour. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 9 to 11 hours or until thickened and dark brown, stirring occasionally. (Stir more frequently as it thickens to prevent sticking.) Uncover and cook on low 1 hour longer. If desired, stir with a wire whisk until smooth. Makes 4 pints.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Make 2 loaves or one 9 x 13-inch cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for 6 small loaf pans.
Check with toothpick for doneness.

title: brownies 2
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add cocoa and flour, then nuts and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until leaves edge of pan.
Do not overcook.
Should be chewy.
Use a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.

title: shrimp filled celery
directions: In a processor or food blender, put 1/2 pound of the shrimp, cream cheese, hard-boiled eggs, mustard and onions and blend to a puree.
Remove to a bowl.
Chop the remaining pound of shrimp and add to bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients except celery and mix well.
Fill celery pieces with the mixture and arrange on serving tray.
Chill before serving.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Blend in bowl and mix well.
You may also want to add 1/2 cup nuts and 1 c. raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: apple pie
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Spread rolls out and quarter the apple.
Wrap each apple piece in a flattened roll. Place on top of melted margarine.
Mix sugar, and sprite and pour over rolls.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake in preheated oven 350 degrees until rolls are brown.

title: copper penny
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight before serving.

title: tuna in spaghetti sauce a la bianco
directions: While spaghetti is cooking, in an 8-inch fry pan saute onion and celery in oil.
Add garlic and oregano.
When onions are soft, add tuna and stir until all blended.
Add 2 tuna cans of water; sprinkle on grated cheese.
Let simmer on very low flame while spaghetti is cooking.
Drain spaghetti and serve with sauce.
More grated Parmesan or Romano cheese can be used sprinkled over spaghetti and sauce.
Time, approximately 20 minutes.

title: buckeye cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, oil and egg.
Beat on medium speed until crumbly.
Stir in peanuts.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture; press remainder on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In another bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk with peanut butter until smooth; spread over prepared crust.
Sprinkle top with reserved crumb mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Cool.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together Ritz cracker crumbs and 1/2 stick of butter. Boil or microwave chicken (salt and pepper).
Let chicken cool and remove bones.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Melt Velveeta cheese; add butter.
When melted, add chicken and broccoli.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix.
Brown ground meat.
Layer in shallow baking dish in this order:
cheese mixture, ground beef, scallions, black olives, tomatoes (chopped) and Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
Stir in margarine and cream of chicken soup.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Add fried onions for top layer and place back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: homemade picante sauce
directions: Pour all tomatoes into blender with a pinch of salt and garlic powder and a dash of onion powder.
Wash cilantro and put about 3/4 cup (still on stem) in blender with jalapeno.
Blend for about 1 minute.
Serve with chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add butter, milk, crushed crackers, beaten egg, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cook for 25 minutes in 425° oven (tastes like oyster stew).

title: jack baird's bread
directions: In a large bowl,
mix
yeast,
tablespoons sugar and water. Let proof for 10 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, salt and drippings. Stir in enough
flour
until mixture forms a ball. Lightly knead in more flour
if
needed
to make a soft dough. Leave in bowl and lightly
coat top with oil or melted butter. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, 1 to 2 hours. Divide dough in 2 parts (do not knead).
Shape into loaves and place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Let rise until nearly doubled. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Heat deep pot and add oil and chicken.
Brown pieces well and remove.
Saute garlic, onion and bell pepper in remaining oil. After onion is clear, add 1/2 cup of water.
Return chicken to pot and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and let simmer for 30 minutes or until rice is done.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine biscuit mix, sugar and poppy seed in mixing bowl. Make "well" in center.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Stir together all ingredients, except flour.
Add flour, a little at a time, mixing well.
Put dough in large greased bowl. Turn dough to grease top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Let rise at room temperature overnight, or at least 8 hours.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Using a fork, beat egg in a mixing bowl.
Add oil and milk. Continue beating with fork.
Sift flour; measure and sift with sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to mixture and stir with fork, very lightly.

title: indian corn
directions: Brown together hamburger and onions.
Drain excess oil.
Put corn, tomato soup and rice in casserole.
Add meat and onion. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top along with dabs of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use 1/3 cup per one cup boiling water in mug.
Makes about 50 servings.

title: beef bourguignonne
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp; drain, crumble and set aside. Brown the beef in the drippings. Add garlic, mushrooms, bay leaf, parsley, thyme, salt, pepper and bacon. Blend 1 can of the consomm and flour whisking until the lumps are dissolved. Add to the meat mixture and stir until blended. Add the remaining consomm. Cook, stirring when needed, until slightly thickened. Add the wine. Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 16.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef and add onion soup mix; mix with other ingredients.
Pour into casserole and bake in 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and beat for 5 minutes.
Mix pecans, sugar, cinnamon and apples.
Pour 1/2 batter into a 10-inch greased tube pan.
(Line it with brown paper.)
Arrange half slices on top of batter.
Sprinkle with half sugar mixture.
Cover with remaining batter.
Arrange apples on top.
Top with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown the meat; drain and set aside.
Line the bottom of a baking dish with tortilla chips.
Sprinkle the meat on top of the chips.
Place sliced or grated onion on top of this.
Combine the Rotel and the cream of chicken soup; mix well.
Pour this mixture evenly over the meat.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the entire mixture.
Cook in 350° oven until hot (about 30 minutes, or until bubbly).

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Beat peanut butter and butter in a large bowl.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy and light.
Stir in flour. Spread batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice and soup mix in baking pan.
Place chicken on top of sauce.
Mix in bowl 1 can soup and water.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight or 12 hours.
Keep refrigerated, the longer the better.

title: one-hour vegetable soup
directions: Place beef, onions and potatoes in pressure cooker with enough water to maintain pressure.
Cook under pressure for 15 minutes. Release pressure and remove cooking rack, if desired.
Drain mixed vegetables and peas and add corn and tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add sugar, if desired.
Bring almost to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
This makes a fairly thick soup.
If a thinner soup is desired, the water from the mixed vegetables and peas may be used as needed.
Yields 12 servings.

title: quick bread and butter pickles
directions: Peel figs and weigh them.
To each 6 pounds of fruit, add 5 pounds of sugar and 4 lemons.
Wash the lemons and cut in thin slices, removing the seeds.
If the flavor of the rind is objectionable, use only juice.
Add sugar and make syrup before adding the figs.
Cook rapidly so that fruit will be lightly colored when done.

title: easy egg pie
directions: Put ingredients into blender and beat for 1 minute.
Pour into a greased 10-inch pie dish.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion 5 minutes in water.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Fold in shredded carrot, squash and onion.
Melt oleo in saucepan.
Spread 1/2 stuffing mix in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Pour vegetable mixture over stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: crispy herbed baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease large baking pan; set aside. Meanwhile, combine instant potatoes, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and garlic salt in bowl; mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in margarine; roll in potato mixture to coat.
Place in greased pan. Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear.
Makes 4 servings.

title: irish stew
directions: Cut the lamb into 1-inch cubes.
Place in a large Dutch oven. Cover with 6 cups of cold water.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions, turnip, parsley, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cover and simmer about 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Thicken the stew with the mixture of flour and cold water.
Continue to cook an additional 15 minutes.
Season to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: st. louis cake
directions: Put chocolate chips in top of a double boiler with sugar, water and beaten egg yolks.
Stir over heat until thick and melted.
Take off the heat and cool slightly.
After it has cooled, add the egg whites.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix everything and 1 cup of nuts.
Refrigerate and then roll in 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll in remaining cup of nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop in hot oil by tablespoons. Serve with honey or maple syrup.

title: corn and chili custard(crema tostad de maiz y chili)
directions: Mix ingredients and turn into well-greased casserole.
Place casserole in a pan of warm water and bake in a moderate oven (325°) about 30 minutes or until custard sets.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat butter and cook onion, celery and bell pepper over medium heat until onion is transparent and vegetables are tender.
Blend in flour.
Cook mixture until bubbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Simmer sauce, covered, for 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf; stir in shrimp and cook over simmering heat or steam until hot.
Serve over rice.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; slice and boil 4 minutes.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion (chopped) and cook 1 minute.
Add cheese and melt.
Add undiluted soups, sour cream, chives, salt and pepper. Heat thoroughly.
Then layer potatoes and sauce in crock-pot. Cook about 2 hours on low.

title: chicken spread
directions: Let cream cheese get to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients well in bowl.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Take out and roll in ball. Serve with crackers.
Serves lots.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in the flour, then add cherries.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: rhubarb conserve
directions: Pour sugar over cut-up rhubarb and leave overnight.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from fire and add strawberry Jell-O.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding with syrup.
Gradually add milk and egg, stirring to blend.
Add nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° until top is firm and begins to crack (about 40 minutes).
Cool 3 hours before cutting.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: saucy peas
directions: Cook peas in small amount of water; drain and set aside. Saute mushrooms and onions in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened. Add peas and serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: magic peanut butter fudge
directions: Dissolve sugar in milk.
Add Karo and boil to soft ball stage. Remove from heat, add peanut butter, marshmallow, butter and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly and pour into an 8-inch square pan, greased.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cube.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix chicken, soup and broccoli; put into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Put slices of cheese on top.
Mix Stove Top stuffing.
Mix as directed.
Spread over mixture.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Take off foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients until creamy, then spread over serving platter.
Cover with layers of the remaining ingredients.
Serve with corn chips.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, eggs, cocoa, flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in bowl of cold water and let sit.
In skillet on low fire, melt margarine.
Add milk and flour a little at a time until smooth.
Add shredded cheese and season to taste (salt and pepper).
In Pyrex dish, place a layer of sliced potatoes.
Pour cheese mixture over layer.
Place second layer of potatoes and do the same.
Bake in oven at 350° until fork easily pierces potatoes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Toss together lightly the sugar, meal and flour.
Beat eggs well; blend with sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 325° until firm.

title: mennonite zucchini bread
directions: Combine egg, oil, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon in a large bowl. Stir in zucchini.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add first mixture to second until all ingredients are moist.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Let cool on wire rack before removing from pan.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, soup, onion, celery, milk and 2/3 of noodles.
Turn into buttered casserole.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tuna fish canapes
directions: Drain tuna and combine with other ingredients.
Stack on your favorite canape base.

title: festive fruit punch
directions: In a bowl, combine pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Cover and chill.
To serve, place ice ring in a punch bowl.
Pour juice mixture over ring.
Slowly pour ginger ale down side of punch bowl.
Makes 18 (4 ounce) servings.

title: cream cheese log
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature, then add sour cream, onions, garlic powder and a little dried beef.
Shape into a log and roll in remainder of the chopped dried beef.
Chill and serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain hearts.
Blend in blender until mixture is semi-smooth. Warm dip in oven or microwave.
Serve with crackers.

title: mama's mexican cornbread(beulah thomas)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased skillet or muffin rings.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: In a large casserole, place pork chops. Add rice, water and soup. Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs, oil and water.
Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Grease and flour pans.
Check it at 50 minutes. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: creamy mustard sauce for ham
directions: Saute the onions and peppers in butter in a medium size saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Cook over medium heat for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk and water. Cook over medium heat and stir constantly until the mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in mustard and salt.
Serve over the ham.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients. Fry in skillet until brown.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in large mixing bowl. Mix well. Shape into loaf and place in baking dish.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Combine cooked ground beef, onion, taco seasoning mix and salt in pan.
Stir in tomato sauce and water.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Cover bottom of small frying pan with 1/4 of oil.
Fry tortillas quickly, one at a time, on both sides.
Drain on a paper towel and spread with 1 tablespoon of meat sauce.
Place tortilla (sauce side down) in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with 1/4 cup meat mixture and roll. Continue using all tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese, onions and remaining meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until all cheese melts.
Top with sour cream and tomatoes.

title: carolina treet barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Brush on any
meat
before
and
during
grilling. Enjoy!

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Heat 3 tablespoons margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Cook onion in margarine, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Spread potatoes in the casserole dish.
Pour sauce over top.
Dot with 1 tablespoon margarine. Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 60 to 70 minutes longer, until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy, about 5 minutes, at high speed.
Blend in melted chocolate.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with ice water. Beat well after each addition.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 2 (9-inch) round pans, greased.
Top with Chocolate Satin Frosting.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain really well.
Mix sour cream, onion soup mix and butter.
Add to spinach. Pour into greased casserole dish and top with stuffing mix that has been tossed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: In a large bowl mix flour, sugar and salt.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil, stirring constantly, water, margarine and cocoa. Pour mix over first ingredients.
Add eggs, beating well each time. Mix soda and buttermilk together and add to mixture.
Add vanilla. Pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. collier's sour cream cookies
directions: Add the soda to the sour cream and then mix all the ingredients together.
Chill dough overnight before making cut out cookies.
Can make drop cookies with a teaspoon and then mash with a glass, dipped in sugar.

title: ranch-style baked beans
directions: In large skillet, melt butter and brown meat.
Stir in soup mix, beans, catsup, water, mustard and vinegar.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole or bean pot.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: boiled crawfish
directions: Place crawfish in large tub.
Add 1/3 box of salt and enough water to cover crawfish.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Drain well.
In a large pot, have enough water to cover crawfish.
Add other ingredients except salt and crawfish.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add crawfish; let boil for 5 minutes.
Turn heat off and let soak for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; slice thinly.
Place in casserole dish.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Add soup and 1 can water.
Bake until done.
Add cheese slices and cracker crumbs.
Brown in oven.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, Eagle Brand milk and half of Cool Whip with a spoon until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Pour rest of Cool Whip on top of pie.
Can be served immediately.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients except topping.
Put in casserole dish and chill overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with water.
rinse, drain, chop and stir in the sauerkraut.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon, let cool.
Crumble; set aside (save fat).
Peel and cut potatoes.
Cook, cool and set aside.
Take fat from bacon, add oil if necessary to make up difference (you need 3/4 cup).
Saute celery and onion in fat approximately 3 minutes.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Simmer approximately 1 minute.
Add water, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Should be slightly thick.
If not, add a little more flour.
Add parsley.
Simmer approximately 1 minute. Oil lasagna pan.
Pour dressing over potatoes.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325° until bubbles.
Serve warm, not hot.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, nuts and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Work (with hands) into first mixture.
Form into rolls.
Place in icebox.
Slice thin and bake at 300°.

title: rice krispies goowie caramel bars
directions: Mix well. Pour over Rice Krispies.
Put remaining Rice Krispies on top.

title: cheese and spinach loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mold into loaf.
Bake in a greased baking pan in a moderate oven at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Serve with slices of hard-boiled eggs.

title: frozen cranberry
directions: Strain pineapple; combine cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Then stir together sour cream and sugar; combine all ingredients. Freeze in refrigerator trays or glass Pyrex dish until frozen. Scoop and serve.

title: swedish butter cookies
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift again.
In mixing bowl, cream butter.
Add sugar gradually; cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Add flour, a small amount at a time. Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and blend.
Press through cookie press and decorate with colored sugar or candied cherries.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 4 to 5 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: sweet southern salad dressing
directions: Place the sugar, mustard, salt, onions and vinegar in a blender or food processor; blend until smooth.
In a steady stream, pour in vegetable oil and continue to blend until thick. Add poppy seed or pecans.
Keep covered in refrigerator.
Makes about 4 quarts.
(This dressing will keep indefinitely.)

title: cherry pineapple cake
directions: Stir the first 4 ingredients together.
Add nuts and coconut. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 16 glass baking dish.
Mix together the pumpkin, eggs spices, sugar and milk.
Pour this mixture into the pan.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix on the top of the pumpkin mixture.
Sprinkle the pecans on top of the cake mix.
Drizzle the melted butter over the top of the cake.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In a large bowl of an electric mixer, cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg is added.
Blend in sour cream. Add flour with soda mixed in.
Mix well. Add extract.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours. Cool for 15 to 20 minutes before removing.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease an oblong baking dish.
Put in ingredients in order given, just sprinkling the cake mix on top of the pie filling.
Add nuts and pour the melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Spoon out to serve.
Whipped cream is delicious on top.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix cheese and margarine at room temperature.
Add milk and mix well.
Add onion, broccoli and eggs, that have been beaten. Mix all of this very well.
Next, blend in the bread mixes and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. The bread should be done but not hard.
It will be a little soft in the center.

title: picante salsa
directions: Use gallon glass jar to mix and store.
Flavors blend after 12 to 24 hours.
Shake jar before each use.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.
Makes 1 gallon.
Good with Mexican food or as a dip for nacho chips.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: With fork, blend eggs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 375° for about 40 minutes, until brown.

title: noodles verde
directions: Mix the flour and salt together in a medium-size mixing bowl. Combine the rest of the ingredients and stir into flour.
Mix well.
If dough is sticky, add a little more flour.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Roll as thin as possible with a floured, covered rolling pin.
Let stand 45 minutes.
Cut into desired sized noodles.
Put into tightly covered container to store. Cook in 2 quarts boiling water 8 to 10 minutes or until just tender.
Drain.

title: green beans with sour cream sauce
directions: Tips: Purchase fresh beans that are tender and velvety to the touch, not tough or wilted looking. If you wish, use 2 (10 ounce) packages frozen green beans, cooked to package directions.

title: chinese salad
directions: Shred cabbage; add chicken, noodles and onion.
Sprinkle contents of flavored packet from noodles over all.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil; pour over mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours.

title: microwave one-step chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in microwave-safe 2-quart casserole. Cover; micro-cook on High 5 minutes.
Stir to break up meat. Micro-cook 20 more minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
If meat is less lean, micro-cook first and drain off fat first.

title: grandma's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients; fold in shortening.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Add buttermilk, knead on floured board.
Roll and cut biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries in food processor and place in large bowl. Pour 1 cup sugar over cranberries. Pour crushed pineapple over sugar and cranberries.
Set aside.

title: marshmallow candy
directions: Melt caramels, oleo and Eagle Brand milk in double boiler. Dip marshmallows into melted mixture, then roll in Rice Krispies. Makes approximately 60.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a small pan melt butter.
Add both sugars.
Mix the flour, soda and salt in a mixing bowl. In a small bowl, beat the egg lightly with a fork, then add the egg and vanilla to the butter mixture.
Now add the butter mixture to the flour mixture.
Stir. Add chocolate chips and nuts (optional).
Stir until all mixed. Put in refrigerator for an hour.
Set oven to 375°.
Bake the cookies for 12 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Cool.
Enjoy!

title: potato soup
directions: Saute green onions and onion in butter until tender.
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Add potatoes and cook until tender, then mix in pot.
Add half and half and season to taste.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple (keep juice).
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in water and pineapple juice.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Put butter in frying pan and saute chopped onion and green pepper.
Mix soup, milk and cubed cheese.
Put noodles in greased casserole.
Layer with sauteed onion and pepper.
Cover with soup mixture.
Top with 1/4 cup bread crumbs, mixed with 1 tablespoon butter (optional).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through and brown.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Beat confectioners sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla for 20 minutes.
Pour over graham cracker crust, then pour 4 cups blueberry pie filling over butter, egg and sugar mixture.
Then make top layer of large Cool Whip and 1 cup finely chopped pecans. Cook blueberries 30 minutes with 1 cup sugar.
Then add a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup flour to blueberries.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add egg, milk and oil.
Stir with fork until smooth and dry ingredients are moistened.
DO NOT OVERBEAT.
Bake in greased 8 inch pan at 425 for 20-25 minutes. Serve with chili or other hot soup.
Delicious sliced with butter and honey or jelly.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 11 x 17-inch large sheet pan.

title: herb marinated chicken
directions: Stir together mayonnaise, wine, garlic, onion and seasonings. Pour marinade over chicken, reserving 1 cup.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Grease a 3-quart casserole.
Mix sugar and spices in a small bowl.
Place half of potatoes in casserole.
Top with half of the applesauce.
Add half of the lemon juice and butter.
Sprinkle with half of sugar mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered, and 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add brown sugar, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Slowly stir in chocolate morsels.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese squares(freezes well)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs in bowl and add all other ingredients; mix well.
Add to melted margarine in pan.
Mix together so that mixture has absorbed margarine.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes.
Toothpick should come out fairly clean when inserted.

title: sugar pickles
directions: Step 1:
Add 4 cups coarse salt to 2 gallons water.
Let dissolve good.
Fill a 4-gallon churn with medium size cucumbers. Cover with brine.
Soak for 7 days.

title: baked apples and sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil or steam potatoes until tender. Remove skin and cut lengthwise into slices.
Peel and core apples and slice into rings.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix ingredients well before adding cheese.
Store in refrigerator at least 8 hours before serving with salad.

title: broiled liver and onions
directions: Preheat broiler.
Heat skillet; spray well with non-stick vegetable spray and add margarine.
Separate onions into rings and saute until golden brown.
Rinse liver and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper.
Broil for 5 minutes for medium, per side.
Place liver on warm platter.
Top with onions and chopped parsley. Serves 4.

title: fresh mango pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in heavy cream and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and top with crust or lattice.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: hash brown supreme
directions: Put hash browns in greased cake pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes. You can put crushed potato chips over the top.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil, sugar and water.
Add eggs, one at a time, using electric mixer.
Stir in by hand the sour cream and chocolate chips.
Pour into well-greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Let cake stand for 24 hours before serving.
Good served with peppermint ice cream.
Cake freezes well.

title: stukas' meat loaf
directions: Take hamburger; add 2 eggs and breadcrumbs and mix by hand. Then roll out mixture between 2 pieces of wax paper until 1/2-inch thick.
Spread onto the flattened hamburger the following mixture: Mix together spinach (thawed), Monterey Jack cheese, 1 egg, Parmesan cheese, dried Ranch dressing and basil.
After mixture is spread, roll the hamburger which is coated like a jelly roll. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 45 minutes, covered, and then 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: corn fritters
directions: Chop corn and drain.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add the corn.
Separate eggs and beat yolks slightly.
Add to the corn mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Drop spoon into hot oil, then into batter.
Pick up a spoonful of the corn mixture and place in hot oil.
Cook to a golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Mix vegetables together.
Crush Doritos and add to salad and meat.
Add cheese.
Pour on dressing right before serving.
Toss.

title: indigo tea shop-sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream butter then gradually add in 1 1/4 cups sugar, beating at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in sweet potatoes and milk.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg; add to creamed mixture and stir until moistened.
Stir in raisins and pecans.
Spoon into greased muffins pans, filling about two-thirds full.
Combine 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon, and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 400 degrees for approximately 25 minutes.
Yield 2 dozen.

title: funny cake
directions: Mix cake mix.
Combine ingredients (except the water).
Stir over low heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Add water and again boil.
Boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Pour cake batter into pie shell.
Pour the lukewarm batter in gently. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Best served warm.

title: creole pepper casserole(serves 8)
directions: Chop peppers coarsely.
Cook in 3/4 cup water until tender; drain well.
Combine butter and flour in saucepan, blending well. Add milk and salt gradually, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Mix sauce with mushroom soup and peppers.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over pepper mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Blend cream of coconut with 3 ice cubes and water.
Add 7-Up, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Mix all together.
Pour into punch bowl and add rum or whiskey.

title: chocolate krinkle cookies
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, and salt.
In a separate bowl mix the oil, eggs, and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients to the wet, and mix together.
Chill for at least 15 minutes.
Roll the dough into balls and then roll to coat in the powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 9-11 minutes.
Makes 24 - 30 cookies.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until firm and light brown on top.

title: spice bars
directions: Mix together.
Bake in greased cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: chinese chews
directions: Put sugar and syrup in a saucepan.
Mix and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and noodles and mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and allow to harden.

title: peanut butter rolls
directions: Cook sugar, Karo Syrup and water until it forms firm ball in cold water.
Pour over beaten egg white.
Continue beating until cool.
Roll out on powdered sugar board and spread with peanut butter then roll in jelly roll form and cut.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat cake mix and 4 eggs together.
Drain oranges and mix in cake mix along with 1/4 cup oil.
Bake at 350° until done.
Mix Cool Whip with drained pineapple.
Mix in box of vanilla pudding. Spread over the cake and refrigerate.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes; place in boiler covered with water. Add salt and cook until tender.
Drain and mix all ingredients together.
More mayonnaise may be added, if needed.
Serve warm or cold.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix with onion and celery.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add bananas.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add rest of dry ingredients, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cut lettuce as if shredded.
Layer next ingredients over lettuce.
Spread mayonnaise over all.
Sprinkle with sugar. Sprinkle shredded cheese and bacon over this.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Cook celery and onion until slightly done.
Combine other ingredients and simmer until done.
Makes about 30 servings.

title: pineapple zucchini jam
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and boil for 20 minutes.
Remove from stove and add 2 small boxes of apricot Jell-O.
Cool.
Put into jars or freezer boxes and freeze.

title: pork chops and stuffing
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in ovenproof skillet.
Pour off drippings.
Mix bread cubes, onion, butter, 1/4 cup water and poultry seasoning.
Place a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend mushroom soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: spicy eggplant oriental
directions: In nonstick skillet, heat oils.
Add eggplant, green onions, ginger root and garlic and cook over medium-high heat for 1 to 2 minutes.
In small bowl, add remaining ingredients and stir.
Add to skillet.
Cook on high, stirring occasionally until eggplant is tender, 4 to 5 minutes.
Serves 2.
Contains 116 calories, 5 gm fat and 776 mg sodium.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cut cooked carrots in lengthwise strips.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Mix the water, onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots.
Top with mixture of bread crumbs, butter and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish with minced parsley.

title: no peek beef
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In an 8-inch square baking dish, layer ingredients in order.
Cover and bake for 2 1/2 hours. No peeking! Serve over rice.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon.
Grease bottom of a flat 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan and arrange chipped beef (chopped up) on bottom.
Place chicken on beef and pour mixture of soup and sour cream over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 275°. Serves 8.

title: beer batter(this recipe makes a great batter for fish, chicken, pork chops,
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together well.
Dip meat into batter, then fry in hot grease or Fry Daddy.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Bring hot water to a high bubbly boil. Stir in 1/2 cup boiling water to corn meal, mixing thoroughly
until smooth, not soup. Stir in salt. Spoon up into a ball and pat into a patty (rinse hands in cold water between patties). Place patty in hot oil over medium heat. Brown both sides.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Combine corn, eggs, sugar and flour in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into baking dish over melted margarine.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Butter a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sugar and corn syrup in a 4-quart saucepan until it begins to boil.
Turn off heat, then mix in the peanut butter until creamy.
Stir in Rice Krispies. Spread mixture in a buttered 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate morsels and butterscotch morsels.
Spread on top of Rice Krispies mixture.
Cut into slices and enjoy.

title: sweet potato waffles
directions: Preheat
large
nonstick
skillet
over
medium
heat. Combine
slightly
beaten egg white, cooled sweet potatoes and milk in medium sized bowl.	Beat until well mixed.	Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir until smooth.

title: punch
directions: Mix frozen juices, sugar, Kool-Aid and water ahead of time and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add 2 liters of ginger ale and 1 can of cream soda.
Add ice.

title: egg in a nest
directions: Butter both sides of bread. With a cookie cutter or small juice glass, cut a hole in the middle of the bread. Place the bread in a nonstick skillet over medium heat. Crack an egg into the hole in the bread. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes. Then flip. Cook for another 1 to 2 minutes and serve.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take stems out of mushrooms so that they are hollow.
Crush crackers.
Add a few bacon bits, crab meat and Worcestershire sauce.
Chop some of the mushroom stems to add.
Mix with melted butter.
Put inside the mushrooms on a baking sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400°
for 15 minutes.

title: homestead cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg, melted shortening or oil and mix well.
Pour immediately into well-greased 6-inch square pan and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 9 (2-inch) cornbread squares.

title: bran muffins
directions: Put 2 cups
bran
in large bowl and pour water over and let stand.
Mix in shortening.
Mix remaining bran with sugar, eggs and
buttermilk.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Combine and mix. Put
cover on and store in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to use,
spoon
into
muffin pans.
Bake at 400°.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: cranberry stewed pudding
directions: Combine cranberries and all dry ingredients.
Add egg to molasses.
Mix into dry ingredients.
Add soda and water.
Pour into greased round tins.
(I use large soup cans.)
Place on rack in roaster.
Add water to bottom of roaster.
Place aluminum foil over top of pudding and steam 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce and fried breaded shrimp
directions: Empty clam sauce into pot with a lid and simmer for 20 minutes.
If adding shrimp into sauce, bring to a boil, add shrimp, stirring for about 4 minutes, lowering to a simmer.
Then let simmer for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix in next 3 ingredients; let congeal in a 9 x 13-inch container.
Cream the sour cream, cream cheese and vanilla; spread on top.
Sprinkle with nuts, if you wish.
Keep refrigerated.
Delicious and easy to make.

title: holly taters
directions: Shake taters in mixture of Parmesan cheese, flour, chicken seasoning, salt and pepper.
Place in a pan.
Pour melted butter over taters.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: basic ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar; blend for sugar to dissolve.
Blend in other ingredients.

title: spinach with sesame seed
directions: Melt butter in small skillet over low heat.
Stir in sesame seed and brown lightly.
Set aside.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix together in saucepan the pineapple,, flour and sugar. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Cool until mixture begins to set.
Fold in drained cherries, nuts and bananas.
Pour into baked pie shell and garnish with whipped cream.

title: beef stroganoff(crock-pot)
directions: Cook on low for 8 hours.
Serve on noodles.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until barely tender.
Arrange in shallow greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Place chicken on top of broccoli. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with cheese and top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve 2 packages yeast in 1 cup warm liquid; stir until well mixed.
Add 2 tablespoons soft shortening and 7 to 7 1/ 2 cups Gold Medal flour, adding flour in 2 additions, using the amount necessary to make easy to handle.
Knead dough and let rise until double in bulk.
Knead and let rise again.
Work into loaves and let rise again.
Bake in 425° oven until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery until tender; drain.
In same pan, add bouillon cube.
Chip American cheese in and add parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Add milk to cover.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Heat thoroughly.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: cranberry juice punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
When ready to use, add 2 quarts ginger ale.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli, carrots, celery and onion in enough water to cover.
Cook until done (5 to 8 minutes).
Do not drain.

title: kielbasa skillet supper
directions: Cut kielbasa into 1/2-inch diagonal chunks.
Combine with 3/4 cup rice, cream of celery soup and water in large skillet on medium heat.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in frozen peas and canned mushrooms, drained. Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese.
Cover and keep on low heat for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour and dry ingredients together 2 times.
Set aside. Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar, one cup at a time, and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour mixture, alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Spray a Bundt pan with Baker's Joy.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift first five ingredients.
Combine remainder of ingredients.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add liquid mixture, stirring enough to moisten.
Pour into two loaf pans.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pans and finish cooling on wire rack.

title: coconut mounds bar
directions: Cut candy bar in small pieces.
Cream butter and sugar.
Then add eggs, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat well, then add candy and nuts.
Bake in coffeecake pan (well-greased) at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: choco-dot pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, spices and sugar.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add pumpkin, oil and bran flakes; mix well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing until combined.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread evenly in ungreased Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Do not remove cake from pan until completely cooled.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: quick raisin bread coffee cake
directions: Take loaf of bread out of wrapper.
Blend rest of ingredients. Spread 1 side of each slice with the sugar mixture and put loaf together.
Hold loaf together with long skewer.
Place on baking sheet.
Spread any remaining sugar over top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes until hot and crusty.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Thoroughly blend all ingredients except tortillas.
Spread mixture on tortillas.
Roll up each tortilla like a jelly roll. Place seam side down in a large plastic bag.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Before serving, slice rolls into 1 1/2 inch pieces.
Serve with picante sauce for dipping.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Cook chicken and margarine in a skillet over medium heat for 10 minutes, or until brown on both sides.
Add the soup, water and pepper; bring to a boil.
Add broccoli.
Cover and reduce heat to low; cook for an additional 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: low-fat zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 (5 x 8-inch) baking pans.
In a large bowl, whisk or beat together Egg Beaters, oil and sugars. Add applesauce and vanilla and beat until sugars dissolve.
Using a flexible spatula, stir in the zucchini.
In another bowl, stir flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt, nuts and raisins. Stir just enough ingredients and gently stir the flour into the liquid mixture.
Do not overbeat.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Allow to cool in pans 10 minutes.
Contains 98 calories, 3 grams fat and no cholesterol.

title: steak burgundy
directions: First, score the flank steak in diagonal lines, a task for a sharp knife. Prepare stuffing by mixing bread crumbs, 1/3 cup melted bacon fat, onion, poultry seasoning, salt, pepper and water. Spread stuffing evenly over the steak; roll up steak with stuffing inside (roll from one wide edge to the other). Tuck ends in; fasten with toothpicks. Tie with white string. Cut roll in two pieces and dust with seasoned flour. Heat remaining bacon fat in large, heavy skillet and brown the steak rolls. Add wine. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender, turning roll occasionally. Remove toothpicks. Slice rolls and place on a hot platter. Add mushroom soup to the drippings in pan for gravy; blend well and bring to a boil.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar until lite and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, alternately with flour; add vanilla. Pour batter into a well-greased oblong pan.
Mark off 20 squares. Drop 1 tablespoon of filling into each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 basic layer cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Sift baking powder with flour; add flour mixture alternately with liquid to the butter and sugar mixture.
Add flavoring.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans at 350° for about 25 minutes, or until done.

title: butterscotch dip
directions: Mix water and brown sugar and bring to a boil.
Thicken with cornstarch and water.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: pot roast and gravy
directions: Place roast on a large piece of heavy duty wide foil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Then cover with mushroom soup and sprinkle soup mix on top.
Bring foil up over meat and seal all around.
Place on a roasting pan.
Cook at 400° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream oleo, eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and coconut; mix well.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When done, spread Marshmallow Creme and let cool, then ice.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat soup and milk to dissolve.
Arrange potatoes and onions in layers adding salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° until potatoes are tender (covered).

title: bourbon ala rick
directions: Place ice cubes in glass; slowly add bourbon and Coke.
Stir softly.
Place to lips, drink as desired.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add sour cream and flour alternately.
Add vanilla or lemon and beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a tube pan.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Soak raisins in warm water to soften.
Roll wafers until they are tiny crumbs.
Mix with condensed milk, coconut, pecans and drained raisins.
Pack firmly into wax paper lined square dish and place in refrigerator to chill.
Top with cherries and walnut halves.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole for 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle second half of cheese on top and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: calamondin cake
directions: Mix lemon cake mix, oil, sugar, eggs and 1 cup calamondin at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°. After taking cake from oven, pour a mixture of confectioners sugar and 1/4 cup calamondin over top of hot cake.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in top of double broiler, add sugar gradually, about 1/4 cup at a time.
Blend thoroughly before each additional ingredient.
Add salt.
Slowly stir in evaporated milk. Continue to cook about 7 or 8 minutes to dissolve the sugar. Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in margarine.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in covered casserole at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.
If you double the recipe, use 1 can of water chestnuts, cut into quarters, and use 1/4 cup of milk.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, egg and butter to make a pie bottom crust. Slice apples and add sugar, cinnamon and a bit of lemon juice.
Place on the pie crust.
Use some of the dough to make a braid for the top crust.
Bake at 180°C for 1 hour.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook
chicken
in water until done.
Debone meat.
Cook macaroni as directed (if you cook in the chicken broth it adds extra
flavor
to
macaroni).
Mix
together meat, noodles and cream of chicken soup.
Season to taste.
Serve warm.

title: icebox cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter.
Sift flour; add salt, pepper, nuts and cheese. Add mixture to creamed butter.
Make 2 rolls.
Wrap each in wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin and bake in 425° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cranberries and chopped walnuts together and pat down in ungreased pie pan. In mixing bowl, add melted butter, 1 cup sugar, flour and eggs, mixing together thoroughly. Pour this mixture on top of berries. Melt 4 tablespoons butter and drizzle over top of berries and topping. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour. When cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: mom's chicken and rice casserole
directions: In small bowl mix together soup, salad dressing and milk; set aside.
Stir onion, celery and margarine into rice.
Spread rice mixture on bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken on top of rice. Spread soup mixture over chicken.
Cover pan; bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Uncover pan; continue cooking another 5 to 10 minutes until chicken is browned.

title: kifflings
directions: Blend well with mixer or by hand.
Squeeze about 1 teaspoon dough in hand and form a cocoon shaped cookie.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar and serve.

title: sweet and sour baked fish
directions: Arrange fish fillets in shallow 1-quart lightly oiled baking dish; set aside.
In skillet, cook green onion and garlic in oil until just tender.
Add water, grapefruit juice, corn syrup, cornstarch, ginger and salt.
Cook, stirring, until thickened and smooth.
Spoon over fish.
Top with green pepper and tomato. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish tests done.
Makes 4 servings, 157 calories per serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Add eggs, vanilla, milk and margarine.
Cook in a double boiler until mixture is thick. Pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Using egg white for meringue, bake at 400° until brown.

title: hawaiian sausage
directions: Drain pineapple but save juice in another bowl.
If necessary add water to juice to equal 1 1/2 c. Arrange pineapple chunks, yams and sausage in 10x 16 baking dish.
In saucepan combine brown sugar, corn starch and salt.
Gradually blend in pineapple juice mixture.
Cook and stir until thick then add margarine.
Pour over sausage, - etc. in casserole dish.
Cover and bake 35 - 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients with 8 ounces spaghetti cooked in broth and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry banana jello
directions: In a large bowl, combine Jell-O and water until dissolved. Add strawberries, mashed bananas and crushed pineapple.
Pour half of the mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let it set in the refrigerator.
Spread sour cream over the set mixture, then pour remaining Jell-O over top.
Let it set in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: delicious peach salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and pineapple; heat until sugar and Jell-O are dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts; pour into Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2-qt. casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda, cloves and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in bananas, oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove immediately to wire rack to cool. Yield:
about 4 dozen.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion and olives.
Spread thin layer of mixture on tortilla.
Arrange 4 slices of ham over cheese.
Tightly roll up tortilla.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator for at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: bavarian salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in water, then put Jell-O in hot water-marshmallow mixture.
Let cool until it begins to congeal. Whip until it bubbles.
Mix crushed pineapple; add pecans and grated cheese.
Fold in the whipping cream.

title: no name salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.
Put in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Take out 15 minutes before serving.
You can freeze leftovers.

title: date nut tiffin loaf
directions: Sift dry ingredients, add dates.
Mix with fingers until well coated.
Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Blend with fingers. Mix in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Brush 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with butter.
Flour lightly.
Add batter smooth with hand.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Fold foil over edges.
Bake at 275° for 1 3/4 hours.
Remove foil, increase heat to 325°.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until top is faintly brown and tests done. Remove from oven, let it remain in pan 5 minutes.
Loosen edges with dull knife.
Turn upside down on rack covered with wax paper. Crust will soften as cake ages.
Wrap in foil or plastic wrap. Store in a tin box with lid or wrap and freeze.

title: lentil soup
directions: Drain lentils.
Combine all ingredients (except tomatoes and vinegar).
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add tomatoes with juice. Add vinegar.
Cover and simmer for about 30 more minutes.

title: tomato-bread casserole
directions: Spread bread slices with margarine; cut into large cubes. Arrange on jelly-roll pan.
Toast in 350° oven about 7 minutes. Place 1/2 of cubes in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drain canned tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Top bread cubes with 1/2 of fresh tomato slices, 1/2 reserved tomato liquid, 1/2 of cottage cheese, 1/2 of oil, 1/2 of canned tomatoes, 1/2 of seasoned salt, 1/2 of oregano and 1/2 of garlic powder.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 40 minutes. Uncover and bake 5 minutes longer to brown top.

title: apricot brandy slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze.
Serve with 7-Up.

title: cheese and sausage rolls
directions: Cook sausage links and drain.
Cut crust from bread and roll flat.
Mix cheese and butter.
Spread on bread.
Roll sausage in each slice.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Slice and serve with toothpicks.
Makes about 40 servings.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut out top of peppers and soak them in salt water beforehand.
Bake at 350 degrees.

title: italian cream pie
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt and Crisco.
Press with fingertips into pie plate.
Bake at 350°
until golden brown. Cool.

title: bruce's favorite hershey bar pie
directions: Prepare pudding as directed. Pour into pie shell, then top with chocolate Cool Whip, then a layer of white Cool Whip.
Drop some syrup on and make spider webs with toothpick.
Top with chips, nuts and marshmallows. Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Slice cheese into cubes.
Place cheese into crock-pot.
Crock-pot should be on high.
After cheese melts about halfway, mix tomatoes and green chiles with cheese. Mix sausage into cheese. Stir until well mixed. Turn crock-pot on low. Serve with chips.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt; let set for 2 hours. Squeeze out cucumbers and onions.
Dissolve sugar and vinegar; pour over cucumbers and onions.
Mix well.
Put in containers and freeze.
Can be refrozen.

title: ham and sausage jambalaya
directions: In a large skillet coated with cooking spray, saute onion, celery, bell pepper and sausage. Add rest of ingredients, reduce heat and simmer until done. Discard bay leaf.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add sugar and syrup and bring to a full rolling boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Take from the fire and add vanilla and soda.
Pour mixture over corn.
Bake for 60 minutes at 250° and stir every 15 minutes.

title: spiced fruit salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well. Cut orange sections in half, crosswise. Add to fruit mixture. Toss gently. Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: country pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil in pressure cooker.
Remove pork chops; discard excess fat.
Place cooking rack in bottom of pressure cooker.
Return pork chops to pot.
Add onions, potato, mushrooms, salt, bouillon cube and 1 cup water.
Close pressure cooker lid securely.
Cook according to manufacturer's directions for 12 minutes at 15 pounds pressure.
Allow pan to cool; remove lid.
Remove pork chops and vegetables to platter; keep warm. Remove cooking rack.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Drizzle Thousand Island dressing over top of first 3 ingredients.
Add tomatoes and bread crumbs.
Drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; 1/2 hour covered.
Makes 1/2-quart casserole.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Combine squash, cheese and next 7 ingredients; stir well.

title: luscious apricot squares
directions: Cook apricots, in covered saucepan, with enough water to cover apricots, for 15 minutes; drain.
Finely chop.
Set aside.

title: lime jello surprise
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour or until mixture is stiff.
Serve chilled.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cut potato into square.
