Put in a glass loaf pan.
Pour milk, soup, salt and pepper over potatoes.
Bake in microwave 20 minutes.
Cover with paper towel.
When time is up, put cheese over potatoes to melt.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Pour into shallow steam table pan.

title: ritzy chicken casserole
directions: Crush Ritz crackers; mix with margarine.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan reserving small amount.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates.
Pour hot water on.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir.
Bake in 1 pound coffee cans greased well. Fill cans 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 full hour.

title: snowy meringue with fruit melange
directions: Beat the egg whites and cream of tartar until a peak forms. Add the sugar, a tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition.
When the meringue stands in glossy peaks and all sugar is dissolved, spoon into a 2 1/2-quart mold.
Pack in carefully to eliminate large air bubbles.
Set the mold in a shallow pan with 1-inch hot water in it.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Remove mold from water and allow to cool until meringue settles.

title: crab pie
directions: Thaw.
Drain thoroughly crab, coarsely chop.
Bake pie shell at 425° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Sprinkle cheese on bottom of pie shell.
Toss crab lightly with onion, sherry and spices. Layer over cheese.
Beat eggs, half and half and pour over mixture. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Add tomato sauce to meat and cook 1 hour.
Add package of spaghetti sauce and cook 15 minutes longer.
Cook egg noodles in separate pan.
Drain.
In large Pyrex bowl put one layer of noodles, one layer of meat sauce, 1 layer of cottage cheese and one layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and milk; let stand until most of moisture is taken up.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat well with a spoon.
Sift together remaining ingredients; add to cereal mixture, stirring only until combined.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in 400° oven for about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; let set a minute or two for easy removal and then loosen with a table knife and tip on side to keep from sweating.
Serve.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos.
Place 1/2 in bottom of 11 x 17-inch pan.
Save other half.
Use mixer to blend Cool Whip, cream cheese, powdered sugar and oleo.
In another bowl, combine pudding, milk and vanilla.
Beat mixture until thick like pudding.
Combine both mixtures and pour over the layer of crushed Oreos.
Sprinkle remaining Oreos on top.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Place gummy worms in cake and watch the children dig in.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add zucchini and dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add chopped nuts.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: hot wings("buffalo wings")
directions: Cut wings at joints.
Roll wings in flour, salt and pepper. Deep fry until brown.
Keep hot.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add vinegar and hot sauce to taste.
Put hot wings in a bowl and pour sauce over wings.
Toss until wings are well coated with sauce.

title: quick and easy chicken and dumplings
directions: In large pot boil chicken until done and remove from broth to cool.
In meantime, roll out biscuits on floured surface and cut into thin strips.
Debone chicken and put back into pot with broth.
Add soup and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Drop dumplings into boiling chicken and broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer until dumplings are done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate egg whites from yolks.
Beat egg yolks.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and cocoa.
Add to eggs.
Add milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add butter and flavoring.
Pour into a cooked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately browned in a 400° oven.

title: guacamole chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt; blend well.
Stir in chicken, celery, tomato and avocado; chill to blend flavors.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes four servings.

title: perfect scalloped oysters
directions: Let beef stand at room temperature for at least 1 hour before cooking.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Rub meat with salt and pepper. Place meat fat side up in shallow roasting pan.
Do not cover, do not add water.
Put roast in oven, cook for 1 hour.
Turn off heat, do not open oven door at any time.
Regardless of the length of time the meat has been in the oven, turn the oven back on and cook for 30 to 40 minutes more just before planning to serve. Open door, remove and serve.
Meat will be perfectly pink.

title: chicken and stove top casserole
directions: In large saucepan, simmer soup, water and milk until blended. Add onion, parsley and Mrs. Dash.
Then add peas; set aside.
Put bite-size chicken pieces in shallow rectangular baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle top with 1 box of stuffing bread crumbs.
Sprinkle top of bread crumbs with 1/2 package of Stove Top seasoning mix.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until crumbs are brown.
Remove from oven and stir stuffing mixture into chicken and soup.
Serve hot.

title: 1 step butterscotch cake
directions: Mix well first	3 ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine pecans, butterscotch chips and granulated sugar.
Sprinkle
over
top of mixture and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spicy six bean casserole
directions: Brown onion, celery and sausage.
Add soup; and tomato paste; add brown sugar to this mixture.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over beans.
Cook in a crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours or overnight. Can also be cooked in the oven at 350° for an hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done.
Cook rice and drain.
Mix broccoli, rice, cheese and soup.
Cook about 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add shortening. Add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix with spoon until flour is moistened.
Cover bowl and put into refrigerator until ready to use.
Roll on floured board to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness and cut.
Bake at 400° in shallow pan for about 12 minutes.

title: mother's lemon pie
directions: Mix lemon rind and sugar.
Add lemon juice and egg yolks. Heat butter and hot water.
When it boils, add cornstarch to thicken.
Combine and put in prebaked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Wash chicken and place in crock-pot with onion and carrot. Do not add any water.
Cover crock-pot and cook on low 10 to 12 hours.
Great after a long day at work.

title: summer yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip together.
Add dry Jell-O (do not add water).
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Arrange fruit on top for decoration.
Chill at least overnight.

title: braised honey chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Heat oil in wok or heavy skillet. Add chicken, onion and ginger root.
Over medium heat, brown slowly for 10 minutes, turning several times.
Drain excess oil. Mix orange juice, honey, soy sauce and salt.
Pour over chicken in pan.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until chicken is done. Remove chicken onto a warm serving platter.
Boil juices down about 2 minutes to make thick glaze.
Spoon over chicken.
Garnish with pineapple chunks and green onion slices.
Serve immediately. Good served with steamed rice, spinach salad with sesame dressing with fruit or custard for dessert.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, sugar and vinegar together in a pot; bring to a boil.
Turn off heat; add bottle of pectin.
Add green or red food coloring for color.
Pour into hot jars.
Let cool.
Good over cream cheese and with crackers.

title: doily cornstarch stiffener* * * * * *
directions: Some brides, when they are being carried over the threshold, can't wait to put their foot down.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop fine the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: gina's butter balls
directions: Chop up the nuts.
Add sugar, softened butter or margarine, vanilla and salt, then add flour.
Mix into cookie dough.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven, then cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: party quiche squares
directions: Prepare pie crust mix according to package directions.
Roll out on floured surface to 16 x 11-inch rectangle.
Arrange on bottom of ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan, trimming to fit.

title: chicken that makes its own gravy
directions: Coat
chicken
with
flour.
Arrange in single layer in melted butter
in
x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 30
minutes at 425°.
Turn chicken over and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer. Remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Combine milk,
soup,
cheese, salt and pepper.
Spread mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Place water and sugar in saucepan.
Cook, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Pour syrup into mixing bowl.
When cool, add lemon juice.
Prepare fruit.
Add cut fruit to syrup.
Serve well chilled.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Rinse
chicken.
Place	chicken, salt, pepper, bouillon cubes and tomatoes in large roaster half full of water.
Bring to
a boil
and cook until chicken is tender.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls into jelly roll pan or large pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, or until brown.
Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley mix together.
Add 1/2 cup of each item, except tomatoes.
Spread over browned rolls. Sprinkle remaining items on top and press gently with fingers. Chill well (overnight).

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: In wok or deep skillet, saute salted and peppered chicken in margarine until lightly browned.
Add onions and saute 2 to 3 minutes more.
Mix cornstarch in a cup of cold water and pour over chicken.
Add bouillon and simmer until thick and bubbly.
If it seems too thick, add a little water.
If too thin, add cornstarch in some cold water and add to chicken.
Add broccoli and soy sauce and simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Place graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine over them and pat it all down.
Layer chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, nuts and coconut on graham cracker crust.
Pour on sweetened condensed milk.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Add onion and soup to chicken broth.
Pour mixture over chicken in casserole dish and sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in oven to let cheese melt.

title: banana split pie
directions: Break crackers in small pieces.
Place in dish.
Melt margarine.
Beat in sugar; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add to sugar.
Pour over crackers.
Spread drained pineapple over dish.
Slice bananas over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Pour chocolate syrup to taste over Cool Whip.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic; drain.
Return to pan and add chilies, tomatoes, all beans, hominy and taco seasoning mix. Simmer 2 hours.
Add Ranch dressing, mix and cook another 1/2 hour or more.
Can be made in crock-pot.

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Layer vegetables; mix soup and water chestnuts and sprinkle cheese.
Dip bread in melted butter.
Lay bread on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bread is toasted.

title: good potato dish
directions: Boil the potatoes until done. Mash with remainder of ingredients. Put into greased casserole dish and chill. Can be made ahead and frozen or kept in refrigerator for 3-4 days. Defrost or bring to room temperature before baking. Bake in 350 degree oven for 30-45 minutes. Enjoy, good!

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken in water until done, approximately 30 to 40 minutes. Debone chicken and cut chicken into small pieces.

Place 1/2 of chicken pieces into a greased 3 to 4-quart casserole dish. Layer half of onion, half cheese, then half of crushed chips over chicken. Combine soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes; pour 1/2 mixture over chicken mixture. Repeat layering once more with chicken, onion, cheese, chips and last soup mixture. Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Garnish top of casserole with a few chips.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, then stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat well until blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 5 minutes.
(For firmer crust, bake at 375° for 8 minutes; cool.)

title: popovers(good with beef burgundy)
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Generously grease six, 6 oz. custard cups. Beat eggs slightly; beat in flour, milk and salt just until smooth (do not over beat).

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°F.
Line twelve 3-inch or fourteen 2 1/2-inch muffin-pan cups with paper liners.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water 5 to 10 minutes; drain well. Combine in another bowl the eggs, soup, mayonnaise and cheese. Put broccoli in casserole dish.
Add chicken breasts (cut up). Pour sauce mixture over all.
Add cracker crumbs and several pats of butter on top of cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan(s).
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In small pan on lowest temperature on stove; mix and heat brown sugar, butter and vanilla.
Cut biscuits into fourths or sixths and roll in sugar mixture.
(I do a few at a time and shake in a Tupperware container with a lid.)
Layer in greased Bundt pan.
Leftover sugar mixture mix with ingredients in saucepan.

Pour mixture in saucepan over biscuits in Bundt pan(s). The finely chopped nuts can be added intermittently while layering the biscuits or the nuts can be added to the greased pan before adding the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put on a plate while still hot.
(Be careful of dripping syrup mixture.)

title: beef and bean burgers
directions: Brown and drain ground meat.
Stir in baked beans, ketchup, onion, mustard and salt.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable spray. Press biscuits out to 1/8 inch thick, using bottom of a glass. Spoon 1/3 cup of beef mixture onto each biscuit and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5 x 4-inch loaf pan with nonstick coating.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon in mixing bowl.
In another bowl, whisk together applesauce, sugar, egg whites, banana and vanilla.
Add flour mixture all at once and stir to blend.
Pour batter into prepared loaf pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool bread completely before slicing. Yields 16 slices.

title: gola maw chow
directions: Saut meat and onions.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients. Then add meat mixture and place in Dutch oven.
Cover with tin foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.
Can use casserole dish in place of dutch oven.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prick pastry shell to prevent
puffing.
Saute onion in butter and place in bottom of unbaked shell.
Cook and crumble bacon. Mix all ingredients and
pour
over
onions
in shell. Bake.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg.
Mix soda with applesauce and add.
Add flour and spices, then remainder.
Pour in greased muffin pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy macaroons
directions: Mix
first
3 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet;
press
with
cherry.
Bake
10 minutes at 350°. If it makes you happy, add chocolate chips and nuts.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Place buttered diced bread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, then sprinkle cooked bacon (sausage) as a second layer.
Sprinkle cheese as a third layer.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard; pour over layered ingredients.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut squares
directions: Bring sugar and
milk to a boil (medium heat;
stirring frequently).
Add coconut
and
cook WITHOUT STIRRING until it will form a very
soft
ball
in cold water.
Remove from heat and let sit
until nearly cold, then stir briskly until thick. Pour quickly into well-buttered pan.
Cut into desired squares or bars.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Add sugar, butter and cream. Boil over medium heat until mixture reaches soft-ball stage. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, vanilla and marshmallows. Stir until candy begins to lose the shine. Pour into buttered pan. Cut into squares when cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, salt and pepper, sauteed onions, sour cream, grated carrot and soup. Melt 1 stick of margarine; mix in stuffing. Line casserole dish with half of stuffing mix. Fill casserole dish with squash mix and top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: drunken dogs
directions: Cook ingredients in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
May also use crock-pot.

title: honeymoon cake
directions: Bake cake and cool.
Drain pineapple and spread on cool cake. Beat instant pudding, cream cheese and milk until thick.
Pour this on top of pineapple.
Take 2 envelopes of whipped topping and beat to peaks.
Spread on top of pudding.
Last, sprinkle coconut over top.
Keep cake refrigerated.

title: chocolate chippers(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the Crisco, sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together the dry ingredients. Stir into creamed mixture; blend well.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop from tablespoon 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from sheet to cool.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 3-quart greased casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 50 minutes.

title: homemade manwich
directions: Combine onion, pepper & hamburger, cook in a covered pan stirring frequently until done. Drain grease. Then add remaining ingredients simmer till done.

title: asparagus canapes
directions: Trim crusts from bread and flatten with a rolling pin. Blend cheeses with egg. Spread evenly on bread and put 1 asparagus spear on each slice. Roll up bread. Roll in butter to coat well. Place on cookie sheet, making sure seams stay closed. Freeze. Cut into thirds. Sprinkle with garlic salt and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden.

title: corn and mashed potatoes
directions: Put the corn on the stove.
You put juice in it.
When you think it's gonna be done, you stir it.
Then you have corn-on-the-cob.
Peel the potatoes.
Put them in the bowl and you mix it with the mixer and you smash it with the smasher.

title: lemon-baked chicken
directions: In bowl, combine lemon juice, oil, garlic and pepper.
Arrange chicken in a shallow casserole or baking pan and pour over the lemon and oil mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° until tender, about 40 minutes, basting occasionally.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer to allow chicken to brown.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients, which have been sifted, alternately with milk, stirring just enough to blend.
Lastly, add nuts, which have been chopped fine.
Put into greased pan. Bake at 350° until done. Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: swiss and bacon squares
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and season with milk, butter, salt and pepper. Drain cooked spinach well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole dish and top with a little cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Combine corn and milk.
Stir in egg.
Add 3/4 cup cracker crumbs, pimiento, onion and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish coated with vegetable spray.

title: banana split cake
directions: Line bottom of dish with graham crackers.
I prefer to crush and line bottom with crumbs.
In medium bowl, mix 1 small pudding as directed on box, but substitute pineapple juice for 1/2 cup milk.
Spread 1/2 pudding over crackers, then layer 1 banana sliced, then pudding, 1 cup strawberries, then 1 1/2 cups crushed pineapple, drained.
Dot with 6 tablespoons Cool Whip.

title: really good buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add butter and cut in until texture of coarse meal.
Stir in buttermilk and mix to form soft dough.
Knead on floured surface 2 minutes and pat into a round 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter (don't twist) and bake on ungreased tins at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: canned pineapple zucchini
directions: Boil all the ingredients for 5 minutes.
Put in jars, seal and cold pack 15 minutes.
Enjoy all winter!

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard; set aside.
Beat egg; add onion, cracker crumbs, ground chuck, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup tomato mixture.
Blend well.
Shape mixture into loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
After 30 minutes, pour remainder of sauce over meat loaf and cook until done. Serves 8.

title: salad dressing cake 1
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease
and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 35 minutes or until top springs back. Cool.
Frost with favorite icing.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, white sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, salt and soda.
Add the 2 mixtures together and then add nut meats and potato chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased tin. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry and cream torte
directions: Make angel food cake according to directions.
When cool, slice into 3 layers.
Partially thaw frozen strawberries.
Drain; reserving 3/4 cup juice from the fruit.
Prepare whipped topping according to package.
Save a few strawberries for top of cake. Mix fruit with topping.
Spread between cake layers.

title: baked beans
directions: Put bacon and onion is frying pan and cook until slightly browned. Mix beans, sugar, honey, garlic powder, and molasses together in casserole dish. Add bacon and onions and put in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (casserole).
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon sausage over bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May be made the night before.
Cover and refrigerate. Serves 6 to 8.
Great when you have house guests.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Mix carrots, apple and raisins.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Add mayonnaise and milk to taste.
Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Soften butter.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; mix well.
Add powdered sugar, about 1/2 pound at a time.
Shape into eggs.
Let dry on wax paper covered cookie sheet about 6 hours.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Ice bottom of egg first.
When dry turn over and ice rest of egg.
(I use Hershey bars and chocolate bits together for chocolate.)
It makes a lot of eggs.
I only use 1/2 of recipe at a time.
Make eggs any size you want.

title: dirt pudding
directions: In large bowl, mix pudding and milk.
In another bowl, mix cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Stir first and second mixtures until thick. Layer crushed Oreos, put on pudding and sprinkle Oreos over it.

title: silly putty
directions: Silly Putty is a silicone polymer, originally made in 1941 in an unsuccessful attempt to manufacture a silicone based synthetic rubber.
This recipe makes a Silly Putty type material from Elmer's Glue and 20 Mule Team Borax.

title: sunday morning brunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Alternate bread, meat and cheese. Start and end with bread.
Beat eggs and salt.
Add milk to eggs, mixing together.
Pour egg mixture over meat, bread and cheese mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in margarine.
Add cream of chicken soup, Cheez Whiz, chopped broccoli and cooked rice. Stir until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue tofu
directions: Thaw tofu.
Press out water and cut into 1 x 3-inch strips. Whip remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over tofu and squeeze in as evenly as possible.
Marinate 30 minutes.
While marinating, prepare sauce.

title: racine kringle
directions: Cut flour and margarine together with pastry knives.
Add egg and milk.
Refrigerate dough to chill (will be soft) several hours or overnight.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. Cream the butter until fluffy.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add sour cream and flavorings, then add eggs, one at a time, alternating with flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Take tortilla shell and spread spaghetti sauce until covered. Add cheese. Top with optional ingredients. Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and cool.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in bottom of a large bowl (punch bowl).
Layer:
1/2 cherry pie filling, 1/2 pudding and nuts.
Crumble other 1/2 of cake; add 1/2 pie filling and 1/2 pudding.
Add nuts.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Makes a large amount!

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Add salt and vanilla and fold in well.
Add chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased pan covered with foil.
Place cookies in oven and immediately turn oven off.
Leave in oven overnight.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix fluids and add sherbet last.

title: casserole, red snapper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat fillets with flour, seasoned with salt and pepper to taste.
Heat butter in medium skillet and lightly saute fillets on both sides, two at a time, adding more butter as needed.
Place fillets in individual casserole dishes. Divide sauce and then cheese among them.
Bake about 12 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: new england doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, milk, salt and nutmeg. Sift flour; measure and sift with baking powder.
Mix well.
Add sufficient flour to make a soft roll dough.
Chill dough.
Turn onto floured board; roll 1/3-inch thick.
Cut with floured cutter. Fry in deep fat at 365° until brown.
Drain on crumbled absorbent paper.

title: good plain potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with or without skins until they are soft but not mushy (halved or whole).
Peel and cut up potatoes into cubes in a large bowl.
Add cut or sliced boiled eggs.
Mix in mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Be careful not to use too much mustard.
Mix well.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger, cook onion with hamburger, drain.
Add both cans of soup (microwave to soften).
Mix well.
Add black olives, then picante sauce.
Mix well.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Drain juice from cocktail and pineapple; add to apricot nectar. Bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O.
Add fruit cocktail; let jell.
Mix pineapple and cream cheese; spread over Jell-O mixture after it jells.

title: pork torta
directions: Brown garlic.
Pan-fry pork strips well browned.
Pick out bread from both sides of rolls to form troughs.
Spread rolls with layer beans.
Add pork and garnish.

title: pistachio puff or watergate salad
directions: In a bowl, combine dry pudding and pineapple until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and half the nuts. Transfer into an 8 x 8-inch pan; sprinkle remaining nuts on top. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours, until set.
Makes 10 servings.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Place cut-up chicken in casserole. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Melt oleo in skillet; add other ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° to 400° (turning once) until chicken is tender.

title: cheesy chili casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In skillet, mix beef, taco or chili powder, tomato sauce, corn, onion and green pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Spray casserole bowl with Pam or other cooking spray and pour 1/2 of meat mixture into bowl.
Put 1/2 of Doritos (crushed) over meat.
Spread 1/2 jar of Cheez Whiz over Doritos. (Microwave your Cheez Whiz; will make it more spreadable.)
Pour remaining meat mixture over top and pour remaining Doritos and the rest of your Cheez Whiz.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with sour cream if desired.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and pat lightly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over baked crust.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Cook
onion and sausage balls in skillet until onion is tender and
sausage
is lightly browned.	Drain off fat.	Add mushrooms, rice,
bouillon
cubes
and
hot
water.
Heat
to boiling. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add peas and pimiento. Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Taste for seasonings.

title: rosemary garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Pour the oil in roasting pan.
Place in a 400° oven to get hot.

title: pork chop casserole - quick and easy
directions: Butter 9 x 12 Pyrex dish. Mix the soup and water. Layer in order. Pour soup mixture over chops. Cover with foil. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients together and mix well.
Spread on flour tortillas and roll.
Slice into 1-inch pieces and serve with salsa or sundried tomatoes.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and Italian dressing well.
Stir into remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: fluffy apple salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir dry instant pudding into crushed pineapple with juice.
Stir in apples, marshmallows, nuts and grapes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: ribbon squares(makes 48 sandwiches)
directions: Arrange bread in 4 rows of 4 slices each on large cutting board; first and fourth rows whole wheat, second and third rows white; spread all with butter.

Spread Egg-Mustard Filling on first (whole wheat) row, Cream Cheese and Parsley Filling on second (white) row and Ham-Relish Filling on third (white) row. Place fourth slice, buttered side down, on ham spread slice, then stack on cheese spread slice, then on egg spread slice to make four-decker sandwiches.
Cut off crusts; wrap each in waxed paper or foil and chill.

title: dolmas(serves 12 to 15; approximately 50 dolmas)
directions: Toast the pine nuts in a heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring frequently, approximately 5 minutes until golden.
Cool.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch crust.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in spaghetti, chicken and mushrooms.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: summer banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on the box. Blend Cool Whip into pudding. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and then pudding.

title: frosted apple cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Blend in vanilla and egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Allow to cool and spread with glaze.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix all together with hot water until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Stir to blend.
Put in ice cube trays and freeze.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Mix butter, applesauce and dates.
Heat; bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to first mixture.
Beat until blended, then stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° in well-greased and lightly floured loaf pan for 1 hour.
Test after 45 minutes.

title: molded chicken salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water for five minutes and dissolve over boiling water.
Add chicken, celery, green pepper, olives and salt.
Mix ingredients.
Put in desired mold that has been dipped in cold water, then chill thoroughly.
Turn on a bed of lettuce.

title: three layer dessert
directions: Add to top of cream cheese mixture.
Do the same with instant vanilla pudding and layer on top of chocolate.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: chili
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper together until meat is browned; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer on stove or in crock-pot.
This may be eaten when all ingredients are thoroughly hot or may simmer for several hours.
Taste improves with cooking.

title: chicken tetrazzini(for a crowd)
directions: In large saucepan, put broth, green pepper and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
In large bowl, mix cooked spaghetti, chicken, broth mixture, mushrooms, soup and parsley.
Pour in 2 (3-quart) shallow baking dishes. Sprinkle cheese, then paprika.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Makes 20 servings.
Good!
I third this and cook in long Pyrex dish.

title: cranberry oatmeal squares
directions: Mix in cranberry sauce, pineapple and vanilla and set aside, then combine and mix oatmeal, flour, butter, baking soda and salt until it crumbles.
Spoon half into well-greased 7 x 11-inch pan. Press firmly.
Spread with the mixture you set aside.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Take a generous amount of self respect; spice it with humor. Stir in equal parts of compassion and love.
Measure in a few drops of frankness (but not enough to be bitter).
Blend well. Knead gently and form into a firm loaf.
Bake in moderate oven. Baste occasionally with sincerity and serve daily.
Your family will love it, your friends will envy your skill and strangers will long remember you favorably.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Cool and rinse.
Marinate overnight in oil, lemon juice and Accent.
Next day, add all other ingredients.
Return complete mixture to refrigerator to chill well before serving.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: refrigerated strawberry pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer, beginning with wafers, followed by strawberries, then pudding.
Refrigerate.

title: brown sugar bars
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening; add the egg and yolks.
Beat well; add baking powder, salt and nuts to flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Spread in greased pan (9 x 12-inch or larger).
Spread icing on top.

title: quick french toast
directions: Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet or griddle over high heat until just hot enough to sizzle a drop of water.
Meanwhile, beat egg and milk with fork in pie pan until well blended.
Dip bread slices in egg mixture; turn and coat evenly.
Place in hot skillet.
Reduce heat to medium and cook until lightly browned. Turn and brown other side.
Serve with syrup.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Uses no eggs at all.

title: blueberry delight pie
directions: Wash and drain berries thoroughly.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, water and 2 cups of berries in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick.
Add rest of berries and butter; mix well and cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Just before serving, top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In it, combine sugar and milk.
Heat and serve over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boiling.
Then cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and stir until blended.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Score in squares while warm; cut when firm.

title: chocolate ice cream cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat 4 minutes with mixer.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cooled cake can be frosted with fudge frosting or glazed with chocolate icing.
This cake stays moist for days and is so simple to make.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix like a cake.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, flour, vanilla, nuts and dates.
Bake 35 minutes or until done.

title: cold taco pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles as directed on package.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook and stir eggplant, onion, garlic and parsley in oil until onion is tender.
Stir in tomatoes (with liquid), tomato paste, mushrooms, oregano, salt and sugar and break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Serve sauce over cooked spaghetti.
Great with buttered garlic bread.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a buttered casserole dish.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: In large glass bowl layer one half of the cake, broken in pieces.
Then pour 1/4 cup of Kahlua over cake.
Next, layer half of the chocolate pudding, then half of the Cool Whip, then crumble half of the Heath bars over the Cool Whip.
Repeat all layers. Cherries may be added for color.

title: dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until smooth and creamy.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine cracker crumbs, butter and salt.
Spread 1/2 of cracker crumb mixture in a greased shallow baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 of the oysters. Sprinkle with pepper.
Use another third of crumbs.
Spread a second layer.
Cover with remaining oysters.
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Mix baking soda with water and then add gradually to sugar and cocoa.
Stir in flour, vanilla and salad dressing.
Beat with electric mixer for several minutes. Pour into floured pan and bake in slow oven (325°) for 10 minutes. Bake approximately 35 minutes longer.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix Ritz crackers and butter. Drain pineapple. Put pineapple in casserole dish. Add sugar and flour together. Sprinkle over pineapple. Add grated cheese. Top with Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: teriyaki broccoli
directions: Use carrot peeler to remove thick skin from outside of stalks. Cut stalks lengthwise in thin slices.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Add garlic, sauteing briefly.
Add broccoli.
Saute 3 to 5 minutes over medium-high heat, until tender.
Toss in tamari and lemon.
Serves 3.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and heat well.
Place a layer of sauce in	pie
shell,
then a layer of tomato slices, another layer of sauce, then tomato	slices	(2
or 3 large tomatoes). Then cover with as much
grated
Swiss
or Cheddar cheese that you can cram on.
Bake at
350°	for
to 20 minutes (until warm through). Freezes nicely.
I	make
two
and freeze one. (Can use red tomatoes.)

title: bread sticks
directions: Sift together the dry items (flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt).
Stir in chopped pepper and onion.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Mix until well combined.
Pour into hot, well greased cornstick or muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes approximately 14 sticks.

title: st. james coffee cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients except soda.
Cut in shortening.
Set aside 1/2 cup crumbs for topping.
Dissolve soda in the buttermilk and add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle the 1/2 cup crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Preheat over to 350°.
Combine oats, corn syrup, eggs, vanilla, sugar and butter in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour. Cool slightly or completely before serving. May garnish with Cool Whip.
"Tastes like pecan pie!"

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream together margarine, granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Stir until light and fluffy.
Add 2 eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add in flour mixture. Add M&M's and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: oven dinner
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain. Mix all ingredients and put into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: pepper steaks
directions: Use any amounts that you want.

title: vegetable pizza(saladona board)
directions: Flatten rolls in an ungreased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Mix softened cream cheese, mayo and dry Ranch dressing.
Spread on cool crust. Cut in 24 pieces and put veggies on top.
(Use no fat cream cheese and no fat mayo and reduce fat grams from 7 grams per piece to 1.5 grams per piece.)

title: orange rum cake
directions: Grease tube pan; line bottom with greased wax paper.
Beat 2 egg whites until fluffy, gradually adding 1/4 cup of the sugar. In a small bowl and using same beater, beat egg yolks with the other 1/4 cup sugar, then add to egg whites.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into egg mixture; stir in melted butter and vanilla.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and the 1/2 cup of melted butter in a big bowl.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Spoon mixture into a casserole.
Then combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup melted butter and pecans.
Mix well and sprinkle over the top of the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add marshmallows the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: diabetic whipped topping
directions: Combine milk, water, lemon juice, vanilla and sweetener in a small bowl.
Beat with mixer for 1 minute.	Add dissolved gelatin and
continue
to
beat until the mixture is thick and stands
in soft
peaks.
Makes
servings.
Refrigerate
in closed container.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and place in a large mixing bowl with soup and a half can water.
Stir in Cheez Whiz, rice, onion and celery.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cut margarine into chunks and mix well. Pour all ingredients into a lightly greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: lemon-raspberry streusel muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add the yogurt, oil, eggs and lemon peel, stirring just to moisten and gently fold in raspberries.

title: chicken marsala(serves 8)
directions: In small bowl, with fork, beat eggs slightly.
Place bread crumbs in pie plate.
Dip chicken pieces into eggs and then bread crumbs to coat evenly.

title: fettucini alfredo with seafood
directions: Over medium heat, combine and melt butter, half and half, pepper, salt and garlic.
Do not boil!
If mixture appears to be too thin, add cornstarch to thicken.
Add shrimp and crabmeat. Heat thoroughly and serve over hot fettucini.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: fruit compote(russia)
directions: This is a popular Russian dish that will taste like pudding when it is done. Mix all ingredients in a large pot. Simmer covered for 1 hour over medium heat, stir occasionally. Serve warm. Makes about 10 servings. Enjoy!

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon together.
Pour into a baking dish.
Place bacon on top of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: In skillet, brown onion in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add hamburger; cook until browned.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry; trim and flute edges. Line pastry shell with double thickness of foil. Bake in 450° oven for 8 minutes. Remove foil and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add vanilla. Sift in flour.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Gently stir in chopped nuts.
Turn into greased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: prune bread
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: avocado dip with zip
directions: Mash avocados until smooth, add remaining ingredients.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: fanny's baby food cake
directions: Mix above.
Bake for 1 hour in a greased and floured tube pan at 350°.

title: ben's red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in container.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak overnight.
Fry salt pork in Dutch oven.
Add onions, parsley, celery, garlic and bell pepper and saute until tender.
Add beans and liquid in which they were soaked.
Add other ingredients except sausage.
Simmer 1 hour. Remove salt pork.
Add sausage and simmer 1 more hour.
Serves on bed of hot, cooked rice.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese; let it come to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients; roll into bite size balls.
Bake in shallow pan in moderate oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lasagna #1
directions: After meat is cooked and drained, stir in chopped onion. Cover top of meat and onion.
Mix with garlic powder.
Set aside.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream butter and first amount of sugar well. Beat in egg.
Mix in molasses.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion, salt and pepper and form into small balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
In saucepan, stir soup and water; then add meat balls.
Cover and bring to boil; then simmer for about 45 minutes, covered.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and berries; beat well.
Add all dry ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Bake in layer pans or a big loaf pan in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes two 10-inch layers or 1 large loaf.

title: pecan blondies with browned butter frosting
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar, brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter until light and fluffy.
Add the vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
Grease pan. Bake at 350° for 23 to 33 minutes.

title: caesar chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breast about 15 minutes or until done.
Rinse in cold water and cut into cubes.
Cook noodles until tender.
Cube cheese.
Mix chicken, noodles and cheese in large bowl.
Add Caesar dressing to taste.
Serve cold.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add chips and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake for approximately 13 to 15 minutes at 375°. Makes 112 cookies, but recipe can be halved.

title: light cinnamon toast
directions: Remove toast from toaster, lightly spread margarine.
Combine sweetener and cinnamon and then sprinkle on buttered toast.

title: malcamation cake
directions: Mix ingredients; fold in egg whites.
Bake in slow oven about 250°.

title: spinach rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer to bowl. Cool slightly.
Combine dressing, soy sauce and sugar. Stir in rice.
Cover and chill.
Fold in remaining ingredients before serving.
Toasted almond slivers add a nice touch.

title: sopaipilla
directions: Dissolve yeast	in
warm
water.
Mix
with oil, sugar, flour, egg and
salt.
Knead for several minutes and set aside until dough bubbles
(about
hours).
Roll
flat
and	cut 1/2-inch squares and
allow	to rise for 1 hour.
Drop squares into deep hot oil
and
cook	to a golden brown, turning once. Drain and roll in sugar cinnamon mixture.
Serve with honey.

title: arizona corn pudding(easy, quick and very good.)
directions: Beat eggs well. Add flour, sugar, butter and salt. Stir drained corn and add milk.
Put into a large oven dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Stir from bottom up 3 times during the last 1/2 hour of cooking.
Allow it to bake to a bronzed delicate crust. Add a can of green chopped chilies, if you prefer.

title: pickled herring salad
directions: Dice herring in very small pieces and along with the cream sauce in which it comes, combine diced potatoes, apples, relish, sugar and vinegar and chill for 2 hours.

title: hot dog sandwich spread
directions: Combine cheese and milk over double boiler to melt, then add ground up hot dogs and mustard.

title: mock clam soup
directions: Cook in salted water until done the potatoes, then add milk, 3 to 4 hard-boiled eggs, salt, pepper and butter.
Serve hot with crackers and a salad.
Use larger amounts for a large family.

title: hot mushroom turnovers
directions: About 2 hours before serving, in large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup margarine until smooth.
Shape into ball, wrap and refrigerate one hour.

title: cranberry-walnut apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan. Combine apples, sugar and oil in mixing bowl. Add egg, mixing well. Combine dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Add to apple mixture, mixing until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in cranberries and walnuts. Spread batter evenly in loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center of bread comes out clean.
Makes 1 loaf.
Makes a nice holiday gift.

title: vegetable pie(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Generously butter a 10-inch pie plate or quiche dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on bottom and up the sides of the dish. Shake out excess crumbs; set dish aside.

title: red cabbage in red wine
directions: Place ingredients in a heavy pot which has a cover.
Simmer over low heat for about 2 hours.
The long cooking may be hard on the vitamins, but it is marvelous for the taste.

title: cheese olives
directions: Cream butter and cheese; add Worcestershire, salt and flour. Mix until stiff.
Wrap each olive with dough.
Freeze firm.
Bake straight from freezer, 15 minutes at 400°.
I use a melon baller to measure the dough, or about a tablespoon.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Cover bottom of stockpot with oil, then add the meat and garlic, chopped finely. (You may add more than recipe calls for, according to taste.) Cook over slow heat until meat is heated through. Add pepper, oregano, basil and bay leaves, stirring. Next add tomatoes, tomato paste, water and salt. Cook at medium heat for about 20 to 30 minutes. Then simmer for 4 to 5 hours, stirring occasionally. Prepare pasta according to package directions. Place on serving plate; spoon sauce over it. Then sprinkle Parmesan cheese. You may double or triple recipe and freeze several containers, since it takes so long to make.

title: deviled eggs with bacon
directions: Brown bacon; drain and crumble up.
Cut boiled eggs lengthwise, carefully removing yolks.
Place yolks into a bowl, mixing in enough mayo to make yolk mixture creamy.
Stir in bacon, then salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon yolk and bacon mixture carefully into egg whites.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika for color; chill and serve.
Expect them to vanish quickly!!!

title: fried turkey steak
directions: Marinate turkey fillets in 2 cups of lemon juice, 3 teaspoons of minced garlic, 5 to 6 shakes parsley, 1 medium onion, sliced into rings, 3 to 4 shakes of garlic salt and 3 beaten eggs for around 24 hours.
Then, in separate dish, put flour, 3 teaspoons garlic salt, 3 teaspoons of parsley and pepper.
Over medium heat on stove, heat oil, depending on skillet size.
While oil is heating, take turkey from marinade and roll into flour mixture along with onion, then put into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning several times on medium heat.
Serve with black beans and rice.

title: pizza burgers
directions: In a skillet brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off grease. Add tomato sauce, paste, salt, oregano, garlic powder, basil and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Slice biscuits in half and lay on a cookie sheet with sliced side up.
Spoon hamburger mixture over biscuits.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes (long enough for biscuits to get warm and cheese to melt).

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
In small bowl, blend sugar and cornstarch. Stir in vinegar, soy sauce and water.
Add bouillon cube and pineapple; simmer until thick.
Return chops to skillet.
Simmer, covered, over low heat until chops are tender (30 to 45 minutes).

title: taco salad
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and drain grease.
Mix in taco seasoning, then let cool.
Chop lettuce and tomatoes.
Set aside in large bowl.
Slice olives into thin slices; put with lettuce and tomatoes.
Then add cool beef mixture to lettuce, tomatoes and olives; mix thoroughly.
Mix in shredded cheese and Catalina dressing.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: maple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly with sugar.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour in syrup and melted butter.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread coconut in 9-inch pie shell (unbaked).
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until pie puffs in the middle and a silver knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Yields 8 servings.

title: crab salad appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into cooked jumbo "seashell" pasta shells or spread on crackers.

title: date nut roll
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter; cook until forms soft ball stage.
When bubbles pop and hiss, add dates.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat; add nuts and coconut.
Stir until real stiff. Turn out on cloth dipped on cold water.
Roll into 2 logs and wrap in wax paper and place in refrigerator.
Slice as needed.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake at 400° about 45 minutes.
Bake in 2 pans.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain and cool.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add salt and mustard; beat again.
Add bread and stir until softened.
Stir in cheese, mushrooms and sausage.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Let stand several minutes before serving.

title: rum balls
directions: Use food processor to crush vanilla wafers and pecans.

title: cheesy new potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Don't peel.
Slice into 1/4 inch slices.
Cook in boiling water until done.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place a layer of potatoes, cheese and bacon in casserole dish.
Pour on 1/2 of the butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Heat in oven about 15 minutes.

title: appetizer puffs
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature and cream it until it is soft.
Add onion, baking powder, egg yolk, salt and pepper. Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Toast bread rounds.
Spread deviled meat on the bread rounds.
Place a heaping spoonful of the cream cheese mixture on top of the deviled meat.
Place in a moderate oven (375°) until heated through, lightly browned, and puffy, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: arugula salad
directions: Remove stems from arugula.
Wash, dry and chill.
Cook penne, drain and add salt and pepper, basil and olive oil.
Chill.
Mix tomatoes, scallions or onion, Mozzarella and garlic.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add penne and tomato mixes to arugula.
Toss well. Adjust seasoning; add more oil if necessary.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Time of preparation: 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: squash dressing
directions: Season squash with salt and pepper.
Saute onion, celery and pepper in butter, then stir in crumbled cornbread and milk and squash.
Next add chicken soup; pour in proper size pan and bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.
This is a meal without meat and it's very good when served with pinto beans.

title: chocolate raisin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In a medium bowl, using electric mixer, beat together margarine, pudding mix and sugar until combined.
Beat in eggs one at a time, beating after each addition until well blended.
Beat in vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt and beat until blended; fold in raisins.
Pour batter into sprayed pan and bake for 20 minutes (until a cake tester, inserted in center, comes out clean).
Remove cake to wire rack and let cool.
Cut cake in half and cut each half into 6 equal bars.
Yield:
12 bars.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and salad oil; beat.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; beat.
Add grated zucchini and beat.
Add walnuts.
Grease and flour two loaf pans (9 x 5 x 2-inch).
Divide dough into pans.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: buffalo style chicken wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips; pat dry.
Bake wings at 425° for 1 hour.
Turn halfway through cooking time. Combine hot sauce and butter.
Add flour slowly.
Dip wings in sauce to coat completely.
Serve with celery and Blue cheese dip. Makes 24 to 30 individual pieces.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Pour into crust and top with Cool Whip.
Serve chilled.

title: dirty rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a covered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Stir after 20 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all together and season to taste.

title: chocolate pie dessert
directions: Melt margarine in large pan.
Add pecans and flour.
After mixed, mold into pan to make crust.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix cornbread, vegetables and bacon.
Add mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces generously with lemon pepper seasoning, butter flavored salt and paprika on both sides.
Grill over charcoal or gas grill for 35 to 40 minutes.
It is not necessary to precook the chicken.
Can be done before you are ready to serve and placed in oven or roaster on low.
Cover with foil or lid.
My family's favorite chicken.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, Wesson oil and beaten eggs. Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Beat well. Add pecans and carrots; mix well. Pour into a greased sheet cake pan. Bake in preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan Jell-O, water and pineapple.
Stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Slice over top bananas and sprinkle with miniature marshmallows.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: most favored cake
directions: Cream oil, eggs and sugar together.
Put in dry ingredients, milk and hot coffee.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Place popped corn in a shallow pan in slow oven (300°) to keep warm while cooking syrup.
Mix sugar, syrup and water in saucepan. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Cook until a soft ball is formed when a small amount is tested in cold water.
Mix syrup and popped corn. When cool enough to handle, butter hands and shape mixture into balls, pressing lightly.
Yields about 24 balls, 3-inches in diameter.

title: chocolate marshmallow haystacks
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and milk, mixing until well blended.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in chocolate, vanilla and salt; fold in marshmallows.
Drop rounded teaspoons of mixture in coconut; toss until well covered.
Place on baking sheet; chill until firm.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread on cookie sheet or plate. Spread hot sauce or cocktail sauce (4 to 6 ounces) over cream cheese mixture. Place crab meat or tuna (whichever desired) on top of sauce. Eat on crackers.

title: hot tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in covered container.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut the broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces and combine with sliced half onion rings.
Prepare several hours ahead and refrigerate.
Combine the cooking oil, sugar, mayonnaise, white vinegar, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Mix with electric mixer or food processor.
Pour over the vegetables 1 hour before serving. Stir once or twice during the standing time.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ginger kringles
directions: Combine oil and 1 cup sugar; add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses.
Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and ginger; add to molasses mixture, stirring to mix.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Roll each in remaining 1/4 cup sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease casserole with butter.
Add ingredients and dot with butter on top.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put all fruits through a grinder.
Add sugar, lemon juice and chopped nuts.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Ready to serve and enjoy.

title: chicken ball
directions: Let cream cheese sit at room temperature until softened.
Put cheese and other ingredients, except nuts, in mixing bowl.
Mix with mixer until blended, then stir with spoon about 1 minute. Mold in ball and roll in nuts.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Serve with crackers, vegetables or on bread.

title: honey mustard mayonnaise
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Makes 1 cup.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix contents of vegetable seasoning packet, water and margarine in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish until margarine is melted.
Stir in stuffing crumbs and 1/2 cup of the salsa.
Place chicken over stuffing.
Pour remaining 1 cup salsa over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until chicken is cooked through.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: celery almondine
directions: Saute almonds in oleo.
Add celery and rest of ingredients. Cook, covered, 10 minutes.
Stir often.
Serves 4.

title: low -fat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a muffin pan with nonstick spray or line muffin cups with paper liners.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until almost crisp.
Wrap around water chestnuts.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over water chestnuts. Bake 45 minutes.
Makes around 24.

title: oktoberfest ribs
directions: Drain the sauerkraut and mix in the caraway seed.
Peel the onions and cut in half; core and cut the apples in wedges.

Next, layer the ingredients in a large Dutch oven in this order: sauerkraut mixture, onions, apples, brown sugar and the ribs. Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer gently for 2 or 3 hours until ribs are tender.
Serves 6.

title: million dollar pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Measure all dry ingredients into a bowl, then shortening.
Stir in almost all the buttermilk.
If dough isn't pliable, add just enough milk to make a soft, puffy dough.
Knead dough on lightly floured board, about 1/2 minute.
Roll out.
Cut with floured glass the size of biscuit you want.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Heat oven to 450°.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot broccoli vinaigrette(microwave)
directions: Cut flowerets from broccoli.
Slice broccoli stalks and onion. Place in shallow glass baking dish.
Arrange flowerets around outer edge.
Drizzle salad dressing over vegetables.
Microwave, loosely covered with plastic wrap, on High for 5 to 7 minutes. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serve hot or at room temperature as a vegetable or salad.
Yields 4 servings.

title: layer salad
directions: Arrange in order the ingredients in layers, mixing mayonnaise and Miracle Whip and spreading on top of onions.
May be made the night before.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash covered in water for 5 minutes.
Mix onion, sour cream, chicken soup and shredded carrots to squash.

title: peanut butter 'n fudge bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and 1/4 cup peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Add to first mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats and mix well.
Save 1 cup oat mixture and set aside.
Spread remaining oat mixture evenly into prepared pan.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cookies stand a few minutes before removing from sheet.
Do not overbake.
Approximately 150 cookie yield.

title: zucchini quirkke
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until brown.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 30 (2-inch) foil cupcake liners in small muffin pans or on cookie sheet.
Combine brownie mix, eggs, water and oil in large bowl.
Stir with spoon until well blended. Place 2 level tablespoonfuls of batter in each foil cupcake liner. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Push 1 peanut butter cup in center of each cupcake until even with surface of brownie.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Cool completely.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening; add sugar, creaming well.
Blend in eggs and beat well.
Add bananas.
Add dry ingredients and nut meats.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand in baking pan for 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lemon fluff dessert
directions: Chill milk at least 3 hours.
Dissolve gelatin in 3 cups hot water.
Chill until thickened, then beat until fluffy.
Fold in lemon juice and sugar.
Beat milk until thick and fold into gelatin mixture.
Sprinkle half the crumbs in two 13x9x2-inch pans; pour in gelatin and sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Chill until firm.
Cut in 12 squares.
Serves 24.

title: chocolate peanut torte
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, butter and 2/3 C. peanuts.
Press into an ungreased 13 in. x 9 in. x 2 in. baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: ground beef stroganoff(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; add onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Saute until onions are golden brown.
Put in crock-pot with all remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Stir thoroughly. Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours (high 3 hours).
Stir in sour cream 1 hour before serving.
Serve over hot buttered noodles or rice.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Chill until partially set. Blend in sour cream and blueberries. Chill until firm. Must do ahead.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Mix flour and spices into bag and place beef into bag to coat.
Brown meat and onion in skillet. Add all other ingredients, except sour cream.
Mix and simmer 15 minutes after it boils.
Add sour cream just before serving.

title: dinner-in-the-pot
directions: Spray bottom of large Dutch oven with Pam.
Brown stew beef, stirring until browned on all sides.
Pour on soy sauce to taste. Cover with water and cook, covered, until tender. Add onion, pepper and celery.
Add potatoes and carrots, pushing down into water, if possible.
Lay cabbage wedges on top. Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Serve hot.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in pie shells.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs; add butter, flour, sugar, milk, salt and pepper. Mix.
Add corn last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not overbake; dries up quickly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Beat butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients; beat well.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls or drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Don't flatten cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing to a wire rack.

title: cran-orange punch
directions: Mix juice and serve over ice cream.
A sprig of fresh mint completes this beverage.
Yield:
2 gallons.

title: mincemeat brownies
directions: Combine
the
first
4	ingredients
and beat.	Add the mincemeat
and
blend
in.	Add flour, baking powder and salt. Blend in well.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan crust
directions: Mix and spread in cake or Pyrex baking dish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Cook the potatoes in about 1 cup of water until tender (25 to 30 minutes).
In a large skillet, melt margarine on medium heat. Stir in onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour and cook about 2 minutes. Add milk, salt, pepper and paprika; cook until sauce thickens.
Pour potatoes in 2-quart casserole and pour sauce over potatoes; stir together gently.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Top with shredded Cheddar and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: kristen's salsa
directions: Soften cream cheese 45 seconds in microwave.
Spread in baking dish.
Spread chili on top, then cheese, then salsa.
Microwave until cheese melts, approximately 15 minutes.

title: nalesniki - crepes
directions: For crepes:
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Combine eggs, milk and water.
Add gradually to flour mixture, beating to a thin batter.
Spoon 3 tablespoons of batter onto a hot greased skillet. Brown lightly on both sides.
Continue making cakes until batter is gone.
Spread with your favorite fruit preserves or cheese filling, roll up and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: pear relish
directions: Grate pears, hot peppers and onions.
Chop red and green peppers.
Mix and heat sugar, salt, turmeric and vinegar until sugar melts.
Add grated and chopped ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cook 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pecan rolls(makes 24 rolls)
directions: Place frozen rolls in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding, brown sugar, margarine and pecans on top of rolls.
Put pan in a cold oven (gas or electric) and leave overnight to allow rolls to rise.
In the morning, do not preheat; set oven at 350° and bake 20 minutes.
Turn rolls out onto a cookie sheet lined with foil.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Pour melted cheese over Bisquick and sausage and roll in small balls.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: garlic grits
directions: Add grits to boiling water and cook 3 minutes; salt to taste. Cut cheese into small pieces and add to cooked grits; stir to blend. Add all other ingredients; stir. Bake in buttered casserole, uncovered, about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a pie shell at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325°.
Bake until filling is set.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses together until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients
except
pecans; mix well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans.
Wrap and chill for 24 hours.

title: punch
directions: Put all ingredients in 1 gallon jug or pitcher and fill with water.

title: tuna twist
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine apple, pineapple, celery, rice and tuna.
In a small bowl, whisk together the yogurt, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Pour dressing over tuna mixture; toss lightly. Chill.
Put sesame seed in a heavy skillet; toast them over medium heat until golden, shaking the pan to avoid burning.
Remove seeds from pan; let cool.
Arrange lettuce leaves on plates.
Equally divide tuna mixture among them; sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick melted oleo with crumbs.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat not less than 15 minutes eggs, 2 sticks margarine and powdered sugar.
Spread this over crumbs.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Spread drained pineapple over this.
Cover all with large Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts over it and decorate with cherries (halves) and Hershey's chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: Saute onion in olive oil in skillet until almost tender.
Add ground beef and garlic; brown lightly, stirring until crumbly. Drain.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, tomatoes, parsley, oregano, m.s.g., thyme, bay leaf and water; mix well.
Simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, or until sauce is thickened, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti with Parmesan cheese. Serves 6.

title: taffy candy
directions: Put all ingredients
except gelatin in a deep pan.
Put gelatin (dissolved in
1/4	cup
water) in when taffy is about done.
Continue cooking until a hard thread forms when dropped in cold water.
Pour
onto
a	buttered
cookie
sheet to cool until you can
handle
it.
Work	1
teaspoon
vanilla in with taffy while pulling. Pull until taffy is a light color.

title: cajun gumbo
directions: Saute bacon (broken in pieces).
Add bell pepper and onion in large skillet over medium heat.
Stir in fresh tomatoes, steak sauce, hot pepper or hot sauce and sugar.
Simmer until hot.
Add cooked rice.
Season to taste.

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Sprinkle all ingredients onto thawed out turkey.
Roast turkey for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 8 x 8 casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese and vegetable soup
directions: In a medium to large, heavy bottomed saucepan, melt the butter.
Add the celery and saute for 2 minutes.
Add the stock, Worcestershire sauce and mustard; simmer for about 10 minutes. Place in a blender and puree.

(If you don't have a blender, cook the celery until very soft and push it through a fine sieve, discarding any large tough pieces.) Return the mixture to the saucepan and bring temperature to slightly below boiling.
Add milk.
Do not boil.
Gradually add cheese, stirring until well blended.
Ladle into pre-warmed bowls and top with sprigs of parsley or dill.
Serve with warm, crusty bread.
Yields about 4 cups.

title: cheese cubes
directions: Slowly melt the entire block of Velveeta cheese.
Cook sausage, breaking apart until very crumbly; drain.
Add sausage to melted Velveeta; mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch (slightly oiled or use Pam) and put into refrigerator.
When chilled and set, cut into cracker-sized cubes.
Good with any type of snack crackers.

title: betty's special pie
directions: Cook beef mixture with pepper and onion.
Drain well.
Beat eggs with creamed potatoes.
Layer meat mixture in a baking dish. Pour potato mixture over meat.
Sprinkle cheese over potato mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes until cheese is golden brown.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Mix all ingredients except wieners and bring to a boil. Boil 20 minutes.
Add
wieners
which
have been cut into bite size pieces and heat
until
hot.
Serve
in chafing dish with toothpicks.

title: luly's pasta primavera
directions: Slice vegetables; prepare for steaming and steam.
Saute some of the onions, mushrooms, tarragon and tofu in walnut oil.
Add cooking wine and garlic cloves.
When tender, add the half and half and simmer to small boil.
Cook fettucine.
Add egg yolks and sauce to noodles.
Mix the vegetables in and then mix in the Parmesan cheese.
Eat and enjoy.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done, about 30 minutes.
Melt cheese over low heat.
Add
Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of mushroom and cream of chicken.
Layer baking dish with chips, 1/2 of pulled chicken breast and 1/2 cheese sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned and bubbly.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cover chicken with water in large pot and cook until tender; remove from stock.
Cook spaghetti, unbroken in stock, until almost done.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper in butter; add this and tomatoes, soup, boned chicken pieces and soy sauce to spaghetti.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place all in large baking pan, generously cover with cheese.
Bake just to melt cheese.
Real good! Freezes well.

title: dink's catfish stew
directions: Cook fish in separate pot and debone.
Put boneless fish and water in second pot.
Bring back to boil.
Add other ingredients. Cook over medium heat for 6 to 8 hours.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Add remaining ingredients except bananas and vanilla wafers.
Place wafers on bottom; layer pudding, then layer bananas.
Continue until you get to the top. Place filling on top, then top with nuts, if desired.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cool celery for 5 minutes in water.
Drain; mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Top with 1/4 cup bread crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake in casserole dish for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Heat oven to 375° to 400°.
Melt butter, then beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients, except Jiffy mix and stir well.
Add the Jiffy mix and stir.
Pour into a greased 6 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Test in the center with a toothpick to determine doneness; when toothpick is clean the dish is done.
Cut into 2-inch squares and serve hot as an appetizer or as a part of a luncheon meal.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: In saucepan, stir together the Hershey bars, marshmallows and milk until melted.
Let mixture cool slightly.
Combine with the 1 cup whipped cream and spread into crust.
Refrigerate.
Top with more whipped cream and chocolate curls.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Put in blender and blend.
Add cushaw to fill blender, about 2 1/2 cups.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Cook at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cover pie edges with aluminum foil to keep from overbrowning.
Add meringue, if you wish, after pie is done.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Heat milk and chicken broth together.
Blend butter and flour and add seasoning.
Blend into hot liquid and stir and cook until smooth and creamy.
Into a greased baking dish, place a layer of chicken, then crumbs, then gravy.
Repeat until all is used, ending with gravy layer.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: chicken fettuccini
directions: *Use more or less chicken and/or fettucini per taste.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Remove insides.
Boil in water for 5 to 6 minutes.
Brown beef and onions.
