Drain.
Stir in paste, water, sauce, salt and powder.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rice.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Stuff peppers.
Bake at 350° for 26 minutes.
Makes enough for six.

title: swiss steak
directions: Spread butter in center of a 20-inch piece of heavy-duty foil.
Cut Swiss steak into serving pieces.
Arrange on foil, slightly overlapping each piece.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix, mushrooms, green pepper, tomatoes, salt and pepper. Mix juice, A.1. sauce and cornstarch.
Pour over Swiss Steak. Wrap foil over and double fold edges to seal tightly. Place in baking pan.

title: spanish creole sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients and cook on a low boil for 1 hour.
Serve on roast beef.
Makes about 3 c. sauce.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal, flour, sugar, walnuts, dates, baking soda and salt.
Beat eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add moist ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Keeps well in refrigerator for up to 3 weeks.

title: tzimmes
directions: Cook meat (if using brisket cut in large chunks) and onions in salted water to cover approximately 3 hours.
When meat is tender add carrots, sweet potatoes and pears, discarding stems and seeds. Cook 1 hour longer.
Add brown sugar (1/2 cup or more). Turn out meat/vegetable mixture into large baking/roasting pan with liquid from cooking to cover.
Top with Kneidlach (dumplings).
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: summer salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Mix in cottage cheese.
Add all other ingredients and chill.
Use 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan or medium size mold.

title: rich chocolate glaze
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat sugar, butter, water, Nestle Choco-bake and vanilla until smooth.
Pour or drizzle over cake. Makes 3/4 cup glaze.

title: smoked barbecued turkey
directions: Remove neck, giblets
and
clumps
of
fat from turkey; save giblets, discard
fat.
Rinse
turkey inside and out; pat dry. Rub salt
in
cavity
and
over
skin; cover loosely and refrigerate for 6 to
hours,
then
rinse well and pat dry. Place turkey in a
large
plastic bag in a roasting pan.
Stir together soy sauce,
oil,
sherry,	sugar,	ginger and garlic; pour over turkey, secure bag with a twist.	Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Turn bird	and
bag
over	often.	Lift
turkey
from marinade;
drain
briefly.	Using poultry skewers, secure neck skin to back.
Tie	wings
to
body with string or secure them behind bird, akimbo style. Leave legs untied.
Immerse hickory chips in water in a bowl and let soak.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Layer 1/2 corn bread mixture into black skillet that has been greased.
Sprinkle shredded cheese and top with remainder corn bread mixture.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix together cinnamon, red hots, vanilla, boiling water and sugar.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350°.

title: red satin punch
directions: Pour half the 7-Up into ice trays.
Freeze until solid.
Place 7-Up cubes in punch bowl.
Pour remaining 7-Up, apple juice and cranberry juice cocktail over top.
Stir to blend.
Serves 24.

title: pear bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat rum mixture and pour over raisins; set aside.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in frypan; add pears and cook 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup sugar; stir and cook 2 more minutes and then put aside.

title: carrot cake with an indian flavor
directions: Use a round, nonstick cake pan that is 9 inches in diameter and 1 1/2 inches in height.
Rub it with the vegetable oil and dust lightly with flour.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: broccoli chicken potato parmesan
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add potatoes. Cover and cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in chicken and broccoli. Mix soup, milk and garlic. Add to skillet. Sprinkle with cheese. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done. Serves 4.

title: speedy sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients until well blended. Pour into shell and bake at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar well.
Continue creaming and slowly add beaten eggs.
Sift flour.
Add salt and baking powder. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to the creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Add extracts and blend well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured large tube pan.
Place in cold oven on the lower rack.
Turn oven on at 325°. Bake for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Do not open oven door.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat egg; mix in other ingredients using a spoon; mix until smooth.
Heat about 1/2 inch oil or shortening in a skillet. Holding your finger over the end of a funnel, fill funnel with 1/4 cup batter.
Remove finger and move to make an open lacy pattern. Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve warm.
Yields 5 large cakes.

title: vinegar baked beans
directions: In frying pan, crumble and fry bacon.
Add onion, diced and saute.
Add baked beans, vinegar and sugar.
Simmer until hot; serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well and add flour mixed with baking powder. Bake in greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs, add sugar, oil, vanilla and squash.
Cream together.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix until blended.
Bake 1 hour.

title: whoopie pie
directions: Cream together the sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix thoroughly and blend in sifted flour, soda, cocoa and cream of tartar.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Put 2 cookies together with filling.

title: granny's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in water, salted to taste.
When cooked tender, drain in colander.
Beat egg with fork (well beaten).
Pour in milk and salt, blending with the beaten egg.
Spray casserole or baking dish with Pam.
Layer macaroni; sprinkle cheese over each layer. Pour milk mixture over this.
Milk should rise almost to cover macaroni.
If it doesn't, add a little more milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese on top begins to brown slightly and macaroni is set.
If it browns before it sets, lower oven.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grilled pork loin roast
directions: Using a sharp knife, make a cut down center of roast to within 1/2-inch of the other side (do not cut through).
Open flat and place roast, cut side down, in a heavy-duty zip top plastic bag or a shallow dish. Add salad dressing.
Seal or cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Remove from marinade.
Grill 18 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Chop lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Add Catalina French dressing to taste or your favorite dressing.

title: cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat on low, butter, cheese and soup until cheese is melted. Add sour cream, chopped onion and salt.
Heat.
Put potatoes in baking dish and add cheese mixture.
Mix. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Brown chops in a hot, lightly oiled skillet.
Place in baking dish and season with salt.
Drain fat from skillet and add soup and water.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Pour over chops. Cover dish and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Wash chicken.
Place in soup pot with water, salt and pepper. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer about 1 hour.
Remove chicken, discard bones and skin.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Skim fat from broth, add vegetables and spices.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken pieces. Serve.

title: double-dipped chicken nuggets
directions: Wash chicken and cut lengthwise into 1-inch strips, then cut strips into 1-inch pieces crosswise. Combine flour and salt in a Ziploc bag and shake to mix. Crush corn flakes into crumbs (can use a rolling pin between two pieces of waxed paper or a blender). Put crumbs into another Ziploc bag. Melt butter. Shake chicken in flour mixture a few at a time. Dip into melted butter. Put in corn flakes crumbs and shake to coat. Bake chicken on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Serve plain or with dipping sauce.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt cheese.
Mix all ingredients together in an 11 x 13-inch pan. Top with bread crumbs and butter. Cook, covered, 45 minutes. Uncover for 15 additional minutes.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin in 2 cups boiling water and add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and set.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Immediately stir in marshmallows and softened cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
When slightly thickened, add mayonnaise, whipped topping and pineapple. Pour over firmly set lime gelatin.
Chill until firmly set. Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
When gelatin starts to thicken, pour over lemon mixture.
May serve with additional whipped topping, if desired.

title: pumpkin loaf
directions: Sift
together	flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Combine eggs,
sugar
and oil in large bowl; beat lightly just to mix.
Stir	in
pumpkin
and
dates.
Add
dry ingredients, beating just
until smooth; stir in nuts.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x
x 3-inch loaf pan.	Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool
in pan 15 minutes.
Best if wrapped in plastic and refrigerated 2 days before slicing.

title: penuche
directions: Place 2 cups sugar in a heavy skillet; cook over low heat until melted and golden brown, stirring constantly.

Combine remaining 4 cups sugar, evaporated milk and corn syrup in a large saucepan; bring mixture to a boil while sugar is caramelizing. Slowly pour caramelized sugar into boiling sugar mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook, stirring occasionally, to soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat and immediately add soda; stir vigorously as it foams.
Add butter, stirring only until melted. Cool mixture about 20 minutes or until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until thick and creamy.
Stir in pecans.
Pour candy into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into 1-inch squares. Yield:
About 8 dozen squares.

title: meatballs
directions: Make meatballs and brown.
Use any sauce.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles. Drain and add butter or margarine.
Mix well. Saute ground beef.
Drain and add to egg noodles.
Add soups and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs or grated cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: cheesy cabbage casserole
directions: Cut
cabbage
into
inch strips.
Place in boiling salted water
to	cover.	Return	to boil and cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand 2 or 3 minutes and drain well. Place
half of
cabbage
in
a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, spread
with half
of
soup
and
half
the cheese.
Sprinkle lightly with pepper; repeat layers.
Top with bread crumbs and dot
with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: oriental roast pork
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients except pork in oven cooking bag and turn until mixed thoroughly.
Place pork in bag after all fat has been trimmed off.
Close bag and marinate several hours in refrigerator.
Make 6 slits in top of bag.
Bake for 2 1/2 or 3 hours.
Makes 10 to 14 servings.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Mix last 2 ingredients together and set aside.
Roll sliced tomatoes in flour, then dip into egg, then into the crumbs and Parmesan cheese mix.
Deep fry or pan-fry until lightly browned on both sides.

title: jelly roll
directions: Separate yolks of 4 eggs from whites.
Beat yolks and whites separately, adding 1/2 cup sugar to each.
Add the water to the yolks.
Fold egg white mixture into yolk mixture.
Add the vanilla and flour; mix good.
Bake just until done.
Spread jelly on while still warm and roll.
Makes 2 small rolls.
Use homemade blackberry jelly for best results.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole with butter.
Mix milk and soup together.
Add vegetables.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp balls
directions: Grind first 5 ingredients in food processor; add rest of items and mix into balls.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Makes 30 medium balls.

title: sonya cronkright's baked beans(serves 15 people)
directions: Cut bacon in little pieces and brown in skillet.
Pour off most of grease.
Mix all ingredients; salt to taste.
Pour in casserole and bake in 350° oven until it bubbles.
Turn down and bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, uncovered.

title: zesty salsa
directions: Add 1/2 jar of sauce and cheese to the crock-pot.
Heat until cheese has melted.
Ready to serve with chips.

title: oreo cookie (dirt cake)
directions: Mix margarine, cream cheese, ten-x sugar and cool whip together.

In a separate bowl, mix together the milk, vanilla flavor, and instant pudding mix. Then mix all ingredients together. Crumble 1/2 pkg of oreo cookies evenly in dish. Then pour the ingredients over it. Sprinkle the other 1/2 pkg of oreo cookies over that. Refrigerate one hour before serving.

title: "no bake" cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter together over medium heat. Stir constantly.
Bring to full boil and boil 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and rolled oats. Mix together and drop on waxed paper.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin and stir.
Set aside to cool. Add ice water and pineapple with juice.
Chill until partly jelled.
Add sour cream, cottage cheese, cherries and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and beer together and pour into greased loaf pan.
Pour 3/4 of butter on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Add rest of butter on top.
Bake 20 more minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Mix
first
four
ingredients
by hand and pour half of batter into
a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle half of mixture over batter in pan.
Pour remainder of batter into pan and top with the remainder of the sugar and cinnamon
mixture.	Use
knife
or	fork to swirl through batter. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: orange almond salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and almond extract.
Shake well and chill.
At serving time, combine greens, oranges, celery and onions.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Pour dressing over all and toss.
Serves 6.

title: fruit juice fizz
directions: Cut fruit into slices.
Put 1 or 2 cups of each juice and seltzer into pitcher.
Add 3 cups of juice for every cup of seltzer.
Chill and serve.

title: mandarin squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Place, cut side down, in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Combine softened margarine and marmalade. Blend well. Turn squash. Spoon marmalade mixture into centers.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake an additional 15 minutes or until tender. Serves 4.

title: puffy french toast
directions: Mix ingredients.
Dip thin sliced bread into batter.
Let excess drip off.
Deep fry.
Brown on each side.
Keep in oven until ready to eat.

title: creamy dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: creole meat loaf
directions: Combine meat loaf ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and place in an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch lightly oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 2 x 6 x 10-inch buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
Rub together with your hands the flour, sugars and butter.
Drop mixture over apples. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Saute onion.
Add paprika.
Season chicken and add to onions; mix well.
Add water and tomato juice.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Remove chicken.
Mix flour with water and add to gravy. Cook until it thickens.
Mix a little of the gravy with sour cream and add to juice.
Bring to boil and add chicken.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots and raisins.
Chill.
Sprinkle with salt and lemon juice and toss with mayonnaise.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chops braised in wine
directions: Combine spices.
Press mixture into both sides of each chop. Melt oil and margarine and brown chops.
Add wine and simmer chops for 30 minutes.
Remove chops to a heated platter.
Boil pan drippings until reduced to a syrupy glaze.
Pour sauce over chops and serve.

title: no-cook chocolate fudge
directions: Sift sugar and gradually add to the eggs.
Mix until smooth. Add nuts and vanilla.
Melt chocolate slowly in the top of a double boiler.
Stir constantly while melting.
Add butter to melted chocolate and blend.
Add chocolate mixture to nut mixture and mix well.
Turn at once into a 10 x 6-inch well-greased pan. When firm, cut into pieces.
Yields about 2 pounds.

title: broccoli casserole supreme
directions: Cook broccoli for 2 to 3 minutes; drain.
Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Set potatoes in large spoon to cut into slices, but not all the way through.
Potato should stay together. Put potatoes in baking dish.
Spread open gently.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 minutes or until cheeses melt and middle is soft.

title: stuffed baked meat loaf
directions: Crumble bread; add to rest of ingredients.
Mix and shape into loaves.
Lay in roasting pans and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in oven until done.
Add a cross of ketchup on top of loaf when baking.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook beef
and onions until almost done in small amount of water.
Remove
bone
from	short
ribs
and chop beef into small pieces.
Add
salt,
pepper
and
tomatoes.
Cook until boiling again.
Add butter beans and celery.
Cook 30 minutes. Add potatoes
and
carrots; cook for 30 minutes.
Add corn and macaroni; cook
for 10 to 15 more minutes until all vegetables are done.
If it gets too thick, add more water.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix egg yolk, sweetener and fruit liquid together in large bowl.
Beat with mixer until light and fluffy, about 10 minutes. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together three times.
Add chocolate topping to liquid mixture; beat until mixed.
Beat egg white with cream of tartar until it forms soft peaks.
Fold egg white into mixture; drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.
Yield:
30 cookies.
Carbohydrate 3.7 g, protein .6 g, fat .2 g, calories 24. One cookie - 1/4 bread exchange.

title: zesty snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cereal, corn chips, peanuts and oats.
Combine butter and honey; drizzle over cereal mixture. Sprinkle with chile powder, oregano and salt; toss to coat. Spread evenly on an ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, stirring once.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Heat until bubbly; pour into a 2-quart casserole. Cut biscuits in half to form 20 half circles.
Place biscuits around edge of casserole.
Cook approximately 25 to 30 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.
Remove from oven and add grated cheese on top; return to oven until cheese melts.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix lightly through berries. Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of butter. Cover with crust and bake at 400° approximately 1 hour.

title: chocolate nugget candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and Pet evaporated milk.
Remove from heat.
Add crushed vanilla wafer crumbs, powdered sugar, finely cut pecans and vanilla.
Mix well; let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Shape into balls or logs, 1 1/2-inches long, 1/2-inch across.
Roll in 3/4 cup pecans.
Roll in 1/2 cup sifted powdered sugar.
Chill 1 hour.
Makes 48 balls.

title: little fried pies
directions: Combine apples and water in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes or until tender. Cool.
Mash slightly if necessary.
Stir in 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon and set aside.

title: cleckner's cheese-e potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
and refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Spread on Ritz crackers or real thin toast.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, jello, water and lemon juice in saucepan; cook and stir over med. heat until mixture comes to boil. Pour into bowl; chill till thickened (to hasten chilling, place bowl of pudding mixture in large bowl of ice and water) Fold in Kool Whip, blending well; stir in berries, pour into shell and chill until set 1-2 hr.
Garnish with additional Kool Whip and berries. Note; sugar free jello and pudding mix can be used for reduced fat and calories.

title: cobbler(peach, cherry, apple)
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spoon in fruit, combine remaining ingredients in a bowl, stir until smooth.
Pour over fruit and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Combine lamb and onion; cook over medium heat for 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients except mashed potatoes and milk.
Mix well. Turn into 2-quart casserole. Top with mashed potatoes and brush with evaporated milk.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Melt butter in a large pot over medium heat.
Add onions, cover and cook until soft, about 4 minutes.
Add cabbage, vinegar and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Cook, stirring often, until cabbage turns bright purple and is crisp-tender, 6 to 8 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve immediately or at room temperature.
Makes 4 servings.

title: christmas-morning italian strata
directions: Night before serving:
Grease a 9 by 13 in. glass baking dish. In 10 in. skillet, over med. heat, cook sausage.
Stir frequently to break up sausage until thoroughly cooked and no longer pink. Using slotted spoon, remove sausage to paper towels to drain.
Cut french bread into 1/2 in. cubes.
Drain and chop mushrooms.
In lrg. bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, Italian seasoning, garlic pwd. and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over sausage mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Cream all of the above ingredients together. Roll into log shape and wrap in waxed paper. Refrigerate.

title: pralines
directions: Mix sugars and cream together; cook on medium heat until soft ball stage. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla; stir until melted. Add pecans. Spoon on waxed paper or spread on buttered plate. Soft ball stage is reached when you drop a spoonful into a cup of cold water and it forms a soft ball.

title: creamless celery bisque
directions: In large saucepan, bring broth to boil.
Add celery, onion, potatoes, salt, seasoning and pepper.
Simmer about 15 minutes, until tender.
Place 1/3 in blender or food processor.
Whirl until smooth.
Repeat until remaining mixture is smooth.
Return to saucepan; add milk.
Heat until hot.
Serve with croutons. Makes 10 cups.

title: kugel(noodle pudding)
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart Pyrex or similar serving dish.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into the buttered dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes (about 1/4 inch thick) and coat both sides by dredging in flour.
Heat oil in frying pan (about 1/8 inch) and melt about 1/4 cup margarine in pan.
When oil sizzles when water droplet added, it is hot enough.
Put floured tomatoes in pan and sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
When brown on one side, turn, salt and pepper again and brown.
When second side is brown, remove and pat with paper towel to blot up oil.

title: lemon gelatin cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 X 13-inch pan for 30-35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and let stand 5-10 minutes.
Mix lemon juice and powdered sugar together.
Prick cake with a fork and pour glaze over the top.

title: hot dog bean casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to
1 hour.
Serve over toasted hot dog buns.
Serves 5.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate and water together in double boiler and cool. Mix remaining ingredients with chocolate mixture.
Makes 3 layers. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Use any canned chocolate icing and sprinkle liberally with chopped pecans.

title: pecan pizza coffee cake
directions: Combine cereal, sugar and yeast.
Stir in water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add egg, 1/2 cup of the flour, oil and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes, scraping bowl.
By hand, stir in remaining flour.
Knead 1 minute.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover; let rise until double (1 hour).

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Shape into ball.
Roll ball in sunflower seeds.

title: fruit pudding salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine pineapple, fruit cocktail, oranges, bananas, coconut and pudding mix.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 15 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chinese pork and broccoli
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Cut pork into 1 x 1 1/2-inch strips.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce and water together in a small bowl.
Add pork and toss to coat.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip 1/2 chicken breast in beaten egg, then bread crumbs. Brown in a large skillet.
Cover with sauce.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour or until chicken is cooked thoroughly.
Remove cover; sprinkle each breast with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and continue to heat until cheese melts.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: crunchy beef bake
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine all ingredients except onions.
Pour half the mixture into a 2-quart casserole sprayed with Pam.
Add 1/2 can onions.
Pour remaining mixture over onions.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot and cold water.
Add crushed pineapple. Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and chill until firm.
Mix cream cheese, Dream Whip, milk and vanilla; whip and spread over Jell-O. Mix the following: pineapple juice, sugar, lemon juice, eggs and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Cool and spread on top of cheese mixture.

title: everything cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash and puree avocados.
Add chilies, onion, salt and lemon juice.
Combine all.
Ready to serve with chips.

title: creamy waldorf salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients in small bowl.
Stir well and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients except lettuce in a bowl.
Add cream cheese mixture to apple mixture; toss gently. Cover and chill.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, eggs, sugar, salt, flour and cheese.
Fold in partly thawed broccoli.
Top with buttered cracker or bread crumbs.
Pour into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 375°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana split cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on the box.
Layer ingredients in square dish or bowl.

title: stoney's potato soup
directions: Pour off grease and set aside.
Boil potatoes until done.
Add milk and cheese.
Add bacon, onion and mushrooms.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut into pieces and add lemon juice. Add mayonnaise, soup, water chestnuts, pimentos, onions, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and put into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle the top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients except onion rings.
Top with onion rings and refrigerate.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: In a pie pan, combine crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, thyme and pepper.
In an ungreased baking dish (3-quart), melt butter with garlic powder.
Dip chicken pieces in garlic-butter, then in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish, skin side up.
Bake, uncovered, at 375°
for 55 to 65 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: holiday cherry squares
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, combine corn flake crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press firmly with back of spoon.
Sprinkle marshmallows, coconut and cherries evenly on crust.
Pour condensed milk evenly over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Press lightly into mixture.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Refrigerate before cutting.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown all ingredients except tomatoes in olive oil. Stir in seasoning.
Alternate eggplant mixture with tomatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: orange roughy au gratin
directions: Place fillets in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a small skillet, melt butter and saute celery and onions for 5 minutes. Stir in flour, seasoned salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute. Gradually blend in milk and Swiss cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Pour mixture over fillets.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until fish begins to flake when tested with a fork. Carefully drain off excess liquid.

title: company cheese cake
directions: *Can substitute 3 ounce jello for Knox gelatine (any flavor).

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and boil 3 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add 4 cups quick-cook oats or 3 cups oats and 1 cup shredded coconut.
Stir until oats are completely covered.
Drop on waxed paper.
Allow a few minutes to cool.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add other ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown at 350° and cool.

title: butter pecan popcorn
directions: Spray a 17 x 12 x 2-inch pan with Pam and place popped corn and pecans in it.
Keep warm in 300° oven while making coating.

title: sage turkey meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch baking pan for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: pig-pickin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and mandarin oranges.
Bake in 5 layers at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: salad for a crowd
directions: Layer 1/2 lettuce, 1/2 cauliflower, 1/2 pound bacon and 1/2 red onion.
Layer again.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Chop onion fine.
Cook in butter until slightly browned.
Add tomatoes, bay leaf, pepper, sugar and clove.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and clove.
Toss bread crumbs in browned butter.
Add to tomatoes; mix well.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix and pour into a casserole.

title: mini blini's
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Mix the cream cheese with the granulated sugar.
Spread each bread slice with 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture, then roll up.
Quickly dip each roll in melted butter and then roll in mixture of cinnamon and brown sugar.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes and cut in half.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mom's soup
directions: Cook in 6 cups water and add 6 teaspoons of chicken bouillon for 15 minutes.
Then add perhaps 2/3 to a cup of whatever frozen or leftover mixed vegetables you have and continue cooking as you dice a cup of turkey kielbasa and add.

Add several slices of tomatoes and at least a half cup of juice or sauce from tomatoes. *Add no salt, but use other seasonings such as Mrs. Dash, a dash of garlic powder and/or seasoned pepper to taste.
You may want to add more water (add 1 cup water and 1 teaspoon of bouillon equally). Continue to simmer until done.

title: iris's mexican corn bread
directions: Sift together meal, salt, & soda.
Combine with eggs, buttermilk, oil, & corn.
Pour 1/2 bread mixture in deep iron skillet or Dutch oven (greased), then add meat mixture.
Top with remaining bread mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; let stand for 1/2 hour. Dip chicken pieces into buttermilk; shake in a plastic bag in which you have combined the wheat germ, potato flakes, garlic salt and paprika.
Place chicken in baking dish (sprayed with nonstick oil).
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes, or until chicken is nicely browned and tender.
Serves 4.

title: brunch spinach strata
directions: Grease 8 x 8 glass baking dish. Place 4 slices of bread in dish. Top with 1/2 cup cheese, all spinach, then remaining cheese. Spread margarine or butter on one side of remaining bread slices. Place in dish, buttered side up. In medium bowl with wire whisk or fork, beat eggs, milk, basil, salt and pepper until blended. Slowly pour egg mixture over bread slices. Prick bread with fork and press slices down to absorb egg mixture. Cover baking dish with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 30 minutes to overnight. Bake in preheated oven at 350°. Uncover baking dish and bake 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from oven. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: pork tenderloin casserole
directions: Brown meat in butter; add mushrooms.
Put in casserole.
Add soups.
Cover and bake 4 to 5 hours at 275°.
Serve with rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, syrup, butter, salt and vanilla. Fold in pecans.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 350° until filling is set and pastry is brown, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: edna's apple cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add milk and stir until dough leaves sides of bowl.

title: mulled apple juice
directions: Heat apple juice and sugar.
Tie spices in bag and put in apple juice.
Let simmer 15 minutes.
Remove bag of spices.
Serve hot.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Saute onions, peppers and celery in butter.
Cook vermicelli in chicken broth.
Add Ro-Tel and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently.
Then add peas and mushrooms.
Stir in cheese pieces until melted.
Combine vermicelli mixture with onions, peppers and celery.
Mix in chicken pieces.
Pour into two 2-quart casserole dishes.
Heat in oven until bubbly.
Freezes well.
Make 1 for now and 1 for later.

title: chocolate sauce for ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and stir over low heat until chocolate and shortening melt.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat until lukewarm.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/4 cup milk. Spoon while warm over ice cream.

title: coffee ring - quick!
directions: Mandarins dry well and are easily reconstituted.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage fine and place in kettle.
Add fat, salt, pepper, spices, sugar and water to cover.
Heat, pare, core and slice apples.
Add to cabbage and cook 1 hour.
Add vinegar and simmer 1 hour longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: how to make your own cream soup
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add 2 cups of cold water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture thickens.
If soup is too thick, add more water.

title: morning rolls
directions: Spread frozen rolls in a 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with dry pudding.
Melt butter; add sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour butter mixture over rolls.
Cover tightly with foil and leave on counter overnight.
Bake in the morning at 350° for about 30 minutes. Turn out onto serving platter.

title: italian dream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar, beating until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Allow 4 large or 6 small shrimp to each person and season with 3/4 tablespoon lemon juice, 2 tablespoons tomato catsup, 5 drops A.1. sauce, 1/8 teaspoon finely chopped pickle.
Sprinkle with finely chopped celery and a few gratings of horseradish.
Salt to taste.
Chill thoroughly and serve in cocktail glasses.
Six servings.

title: mayo cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in one bowl.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Place chicken breast halves between wax paper; pound slightly with a mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: famous yates wiener soup
directions: In a large pot, boil noodles.
Add tomato saue and wieners. Add seasonings to taste.
Boil for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fun fruit dip
directions: Whip all ingredients together.
Serve cold with your favorite fruits.

title: cynthia white's hot mulled cider
directions: Pour juice into party percolator.
Add water.
Mix spices and sugar; place into percolator basket.
Let this to through perk cycle.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Press 1 package of rolls into a 13 x 9-inch pan, making sure you pinch seams together.
Mix softened cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolks well and pour on top of rolls, then press another package of rolls on top, pinching seams together.
Brush with egg white and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs and sugar, then add balance of ingredients.
Blend well and pour into a loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: play dough(not to eat!)
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Add food coloring.
Remove from heat and add the vegetable oil, powdered alum and flour. Knead until smooth.
(Play dough is very hot at this point; be sure to test before having children help knead.)
Store in sealed container.
Keeps very well.

title: nancy's chicken piccata
directions: Rinse and dry chicken breasts.
Flatten with meat mallet and cut into half crosswise. Dredge in flour and shake off excess.

title: slush punch for a crowd
directions: In 6-quart container, combine sugar and gelatin powder.
Add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice; mix well.

Pour into plastic containers and freeze at least 24 hours. About an hour before serving time, put out containers to thaw. Empty containers into large punch bowl; break mixture into chunks with wooden spoon.
Add ginger ale; mix to a slushy consistency.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Combine broccoli and onion; cook together.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Season with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Boil ribs for 30 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cool water. Place in cooking dish.
Combine ketchup and cola.
Pour over ribs. Cook in oven, covered.
Bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.
Baste occasionally.
May cook in crock-pot on high for 5 to 6 hours, uncovered.
Baste occasionally.

title: freezer peach jam
directions: Peel and pit peaches; chop or grind very fine.
Measure 2 1/4 cups into large bowl.
Add lemon juice and fruit protector.
Stir sugar into fruit.
Let stand 10 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in 3 (8-inch) layer pans for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown beef in butter, stirring until cooked.
Stir in garlic salt, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: shoestring potato cookies
directions: Melt chips in double boiler. Add shoestring potatoes.
Mix. Drop onto wax paper by spoonfuls. Let harden.

title: toffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed margarine.
Put aside 1/2 cup of this mixture for topping.
To remainder, add buttermilk, egg and vanilla.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan or glass dish.
To 1/2 cup of reserved topping, add crushed Heath bars and nuts.
Spread this evenly over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: summer shrimp bisque
directions: Blend together well, chill serves 8.

title: salsa
directions: In a small pan, boil water and plop tomatoes in for about 10 seconds.
Blanch skin.
Quarter tomatoes; put in saucepan until quite thick, about 1 hour without cover.
Add all ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.
Freeze in jars.
Makes six half pints.

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Spread cream cheese in a shallow serving plate. Put on crab meat. Mix rest of ingredients and spoon over crab. Chill covered. Serve with crackers.

title: ham potato cheese soup
directions: Place potatoes, onions and cubed ham in a large pot. Cover with water. Cook until potatoes are almost tender. Remove about 1 cup of the cooked potatoes and mash in a bowl with the back of a fork. Add some of the liquid from the pan (about a teaspoon at a time) along with the flour until you have a thick paste. Add back to the pot. Place the cubed cheese in the pot. Let simmer until the cheese melts. Add pepper and stir in the milk.

title: sweet potato peanut butter balls
directions: Combine warm potatoes with beaten egg, sugar and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Shape peanut butter into 8 balls, using about 1 tablespoon per ball.
Press 1/4 cup of sweet potatoes around each peanut butter ball.
Roll each in crushed cereal flakes or bread crumbs.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Dip biscuit pieces into sugar mixture or shake in a plastic bag.
Put pieces in well-greased Bundt pan.
Heat brown sugar and margarine; do not boil.
Pour over pieces.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Let cool for 10 minutes, then turn upside-down on plate.
Tear off pieces.

title: cracker salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding enough mayonnaise to hold salad together.

title: great cheesecake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter with a pastry knife. Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Put 1/3 dough on the bottom of a spring-form pan.
Bake at 450° until brown (about 6 to 8 minutes). Cool and attach sides.
Butter sides and pat remaining dough around side of pan.

title: old fashioned cocoa fudge
directions: Thoroughly combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a heavy 4-quart saucepan, gradually add milk.
Bring to a bubbly boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue to boil without stirring or until soft ball stage.
Remove saucepan from heat, add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature.
Beat by hand until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly spread fudge in buttered pan.
Cut.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix together the Crisco and Parkay, flour, white sugar, cinnamon, cloves and eggs.
Batter will be thick.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Do not overbake.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil corn 5 minutes.
Cold dip it.
Cut from cob.
Measure. Chop and measure cabbage and peppers.
Chop onions.
Combine ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
More salt and sugar may be added.
Pack in hot jars and seal at once.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Layer bean dip in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix avocados with lemon juice; spread over bean dip.
Mix salt, pepper, sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning and spread over avocado mixture. Sprinkle olives, onions and tomato over sour cream mixture and top with Cheddar cheese.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine egg and 1/4 cup soup.
Stir in uncooked rice, onion, parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into 20 small balls.
Place in a 10-inch skillet.

title: potato-bacon soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in a large saucepan.
Add onion and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add potatoes and water. Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Gradually add milk, salt and pepper.
Heat again to serving temperature (do not boil).
Add parsley flakes when serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Butter bottom of pan.
Combine oleo, 2 cans corn, sour cream and cornbread mix.
Stir well.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: beets with pineapple(low-fat)
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Stir in pineapple with juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add oleo, lemon juice and beets (that have been drained).
Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes or thoroughly heated.

title: rice-corn
directions: Mix corn and rice. Saute onion and bell pepper and add to corn and rice. Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle cheese (grated) on top. Bake 15 minutes more.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle onion and shallots around and under chicken pieces.
Pour oil and wine or vermouth over chicken. Sprinkle with tarragon and black pepper.
Cover baking dish tightly with foil.
Bake 45 minute.
Remove foil.
Turn oven to 375°.
Bake uncovered for additional 15 minutes.

title: roast and veggies with gravy
directions: Place meat, vegetables, salt and pepper in a cooking bag with onion soup mix mixed with water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove meat juices; mix in a saucepan with mushroom soup.
Heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Serve.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken; keep broth to cook spaghetti in.
Debone chicken.
When spaghetti is tender, pour remaining broth off and melt cheese in the spaghetti.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Then combine all ingredients.
Place in baking dish. Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cocktail dogs
directions: In saucepan, bring to a boil beer, brown sugar and ketchup; simmer 20 minutes.
Pour over hot dogs.
Warm.
Great appetizer.

title: roxanne's princess bars
directions: In medium mixing bowl, beat together eggs, honey, vanilla, orange peel and orange juice.
In separate bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to honey mixture.
Stir in dates, nuts and zucchini.
Spread the mixture in a greased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken in thin slices and marinate in soy sauce, garlic and lemon juice for 4 to 6 hours.
In wok or large skillet on high heat, add 4 tablespoons olive oil.
Brown meat and push aside.
Add carrots, celery and pepper over low heat and cover for 10 minutes. Add pineapple and simmer 5 minutes.
Add juices, water, honey, vinegar, brown sugar, lemon juice, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and cornstarch to above meat/vegetable mixture.
Stir occasionally until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: butter mints
directions: Combine milk and butter in top of double boiler.
Heat until butter melts.
Remove and add peppermint oil and coloring.
Add sugar and stir until blended.
Turn out onto wax paper, well powdered with xxxx sugar.
Roll into ball and knead until workable.
Take small amounts at a time (small pieces) and roll into balls.
Place on waxed paper and flatten with a fork.
Let stand overnight until hard.

title: seafoam broccoli
directions: Steam the broccoli, being careful not to overcook.
Arrange broccoli in an ovenproof serving dish.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Fold in yogurt and mayonnaise gently.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Place under broiler and broil until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: herbed refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water in a large bowl.
Add honey; let stand 5 minutes.
Add 3 3/4 cups flour and the next 6 ingredients, stirring to form a soft dough.
Place dough in a large, airtight container coated with cooking spray; turn to coat top.
Refrigerate up to 24 hours; dough will double in bulk.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead dough 7 to 8 times.
Add enough of remaining flour, 1 tablespoon at a time, to prevent dough from sticking to hands.
Divide dough in half; cut each portion into 15 pieces.
Shape each piece into a 6-inch rope; carefully tie each rope into a knot.
Place knots on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream butter with sugar. Add egg and vanilla and beat until fluffy. Stir in banana and jam. Measure in flour, baking powder, salt, nuts and lemon juice. Spread into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Spread with strained jam. Sprinkle the crushed nuts over. Cut when cool into 36 squares.

title: old fashioned rice custard
directions: Combine
rice
and
2 cups milk.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until
rice is tender.
Stir in butter.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in sugar, vanilla, salt and remaining milk.
Stir into hot
rice
mixture.
Pour
into
slightly greased 2 quart casserole and top with nutmeg.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: bean stew
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add everything and heat to a slight boil. Keep warm.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Melt chocolate.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in pan.
Stir in milk; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir hot custard, slowly, into egg yolks.
Add gelatin. Strain into 4-cup measure.
Spoon 1 cup custard back into saucepan; blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture into pastry shell. Chill.
Stir rum flavoring into remaining custard.
Cool.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar; add remaining sugar.
Fold egg whites into custard; spoon over chocolate mixture.
Chill for 2 hours.
Top with whipped cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and butter.
Press into a 9x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: old-fashioned date and nut bread
directions: Sift the flour, salt and soda together and mix in broken nut meats.
Add to vinegar enough boiling water to make 1 1/2 cups. Add shortening.
Pour over dates and let stand 10 minutes. Combine egg and brown sugar.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add dates and water-vinegar mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni by box instructions, using 2 1/2 cups of water.
Layer in a dish as follows:
Rice-A-Roni, broccoli and chicken.
Mix soup, broth and curry powder; pour over casserole. Add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press mixture into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Lower oven temperature to 300° for baking of filling.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and sugar.
Rinse jar with 1/2 cup water.
Decrease heat and simmer about 10 minutes.
Cook lasagna with salt and 2 tablespoons cooking oil in boiling water.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Using an oblong baking dish, layer noodles and meat and cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 375°
oven about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: spice tea mix
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Package tea mix in small jars.
To use, add 1 teaspoon of spiced tea mixture per cup of boiling water.
This makes nice gifts at Christmas.

title: mamma swanner's pecan pie
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add vanilla, pecans and vinegar; stir until well mixed.
Pour into pie shell; bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cook meat for 5 minutes; mix flour with 1/2 cup tomato juice. Stir into meat; add tomatoes, onions and spices.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Grease 3-quart casserole. Layer noodles, meat mixture and sliced cheese.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: crispy deviled chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray shallow roasting pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix egg, broth, mustard and garlic in small bowl. In separate container, mix bread crumbs, basil, paprika and white pepper.

title: watergate salad
directions: Pour dry pistachio instant pudding mix in bowl.
Add undrained crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients by hand.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: beef pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, pecans and few sprinkles of garlic powder. Spread the mixture on individual slices of dried beef.
Roll slice up.
Cut each rolled up beef slice into 4 to 5 bite-size pieces.

title: onion soup a la anne
directions: Cook the onions in butter and oil slowly in a covered saucepan for 15 minutes; raise heat to moderate and stir in salt and sugar. Cook for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring frequently until the onions have turned an even, deep golden brown.
Sprinkle in flour and stir for 3 minutes.
Off heat, blend in boiling bouillon.
Add wine or vermouth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer partially covered for 30 to 40 minutes or more.
Add croutons and Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: caramel kick bars
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Spread into greased pan, 9 x 13-inches.
Bake at 325° until done, approximately 55 minutes; let cool.

title: tyler's favorite deer sausage
directions: Cut sausage in hunks.
Brown in frying pan.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with hot biscuits and grits.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cool and whip jello and water.
Combine powdered sugar, oleo and graham crackers.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Save 1/2 cup to put on the top.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip the Milnot until stiff.
Fold all together.
Top with 1/2 cup crumbs. Refrigerate or freeze.

title: crustless zucchini pie
directions: In bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. Stir in zucchini, Bisquick and cheese. Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie plates. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: texas chicken(you'll use this over and over again)
directions: Soak tortillas in chicken broth until broth is absorbed. Spread tortillas over bottom of 9 x 13-inch lightly greased baking dish.
Add layers as follows:
chicken, mushroom soup, chicken soup, tomatoes with chilies, sauteed onion, jalapeno peppers, garlic powder and seasoned salt.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and the mixture is thoroughly heated.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together well.
Put butter on top and cook until nothing comes off toothpick.

title: layered chocolate brownies
directions: Combine 1/3 cup
milk with caramels in a double boiler. Melt and stir
until
smooth.
Combine cake mix with other 1/3 cup milk and
combine
with	butter.
Mix together and stir in nuts.
Press 1/2 of
cake
mix
in
greased
and
floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: freezer cream puffs
directions: Mix pudding; add Cool Whip and beat until soft peaks form.

title: caramel candy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat candies and milk over low heat, stirring frequently, until smooth.
(Can microwave at one minute intervals until melted, stirring each minute.)
Remove from heat and set aside.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and egg in a large bowl.
Stir in softened butter with a fork until mixture is crumbly.
Press half of this in a pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts. Drizzle with caramel.
Sprinkle remaining crumbly mixture over top. Bake until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes. Loosen edges from sides of pan.
When completely cooled, cut into bars.

title: lemon frozen dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Spread on bottom and sides of 7 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (do not overbake; cool).

title: meat sauce
directions: Cook until thick, stirring.
You can use tomato paste and not drain pineapple.
This is great on ham!

title: salmon loaf
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, bread crumbs and onion.
Add drained salmon (remove bones and dark skin).
Mix altogether and stir in melted butter.
Pack into an 8 x 4-inch pan or use a pie dish (8 or 9-inch). Sprinkle crushed saltine crackers on top and bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes for loaf pan or about 30 minutes for a pie dish.

title: lori's hawaiian tuna salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together and serve or chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil Minute rice.
Combine water and onion and mushroom soups; cook.
After soup is boiled and rice is cooked, combine rice and soup together.
Lay chicken breast in casserole dish.
Pour soup and rice over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix the sugars, margarine and egg in a large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until light brown.
Cool slightly.

title: coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sift first three ingredients.
Set aside.
With electric mixer at medium speed, mix butter with granulated sugar, then with eggs until very light and fluffy, about 4 minutes.
Then at low speed, beat in alternately, just until smooth, flour mixture in fourths and vanilla and milk in thirds.
Spread half of mixture in pan. Top with half of brown sugar mixture.
Swirl throughout.
Repeat. Bake about 45 minutes.

title: confetti bits
directions: Press unrolled dough into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries.
Chop apples and oranges fine. Add sugar.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water.
When cool, add salad mixture.

title: punch
directions: Thaw raspberry pink lemonade and add ginger ale.
Chill. Before serving, top off with scoops of sherbet.
For a zip, add some vodka.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken, debone and tear into pieces.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with Veg-All, drained, and English peas, drained.

title: gin slush
directions: Boil sugar and water, then cool.
Blend bananas, lemon juice, oranges and lemons.
Mix sugar and water, blended mixture, pineapple juice and gin together and put in freezer.
Scoop into a glass 1/2 full and fill the rest with 7-Up.
Enjoy.

title: yam apple pineapple dish
directions: Cook yams with skins on until almost done.
Drain pineapple. Stir cornstarch into 1/2 cup of the cold liquid.
Add lemon juice. Mix in sugar and salt; set aside.
Bring remaining 1 1/2 cups juice to a slow boil.
Gradually stir in cornstarch mixture, stirring constantly.
Add butter and continue to stir until mixture starts to bubble.
Remove from heat.
In a large casserole dish, place half of the sliced yams, sliced apples and pineapple. Top with juice.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Put salmon in a mixing bowl and remove bones.
Add saltine crackers that have been crushed; add milk, baking powder and salt; mix.
Beat eggs and add to mixture; mix well.
Dot with butter on top of mixture that has been put into a casserole.
Place casserole in a pan with about 1-inch water as for custard.
Bake at 350° until a knife comes out clean, about 1 hour.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Cream the cream cheese with butter.
Mix all ingredients with this mixture.
Form in small balls and press with finger or fork. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Stores nicely.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound seasoned flour into both sides of round steak (2 inches thick).
Brown 2 onions in hot oil in heavy skillet.
Remove onions and brown meat well on both sides.
Top with onions and add tomatoes.
Cover and cook slowly until tender, 2 1/2 to 3 hours. 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple praline squash
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, place squash cut side up.
Pour water into pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.
In an 8-inch skillet, melt butter. Stir in apple, brown sugar, cinnamon and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat (3 to 4 minutes).
Spoon an equal amount into baked squash half.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Break cooked corn bread and toasted day-old bread together while still hot.
Pour hot broth over bread mixture.
Saute celery, green pepper and onions in butter until transparent.
Add mixture to corn bread mixture.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, sage, poultry seasoning and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch lightly greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: calico salad
directions: Combine brown sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric and salt and pepper mix well.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Hollow out the round loaf of bread.
Spoon mixture into loaf.
Sprinkle more cheese on top. Place on cookie sheet.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with crackers.
One of the best appetizers I've ever tasted!

title: mrs. sanborn's autumn apple pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl until smooth.
Heat electric skillet to 325°.
Coat cooking surface with 1 teaspoon of oil.
Drop two tablespoons of batter for each apple pancake into the skillet. Fry for about 2 minutes on each side, until golden brown.
They taste best warm!
Serve with applesauce, if desired.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil for 2 minutes. Add 3 cups powdered sugar. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Mix well.

title: tomato jack
directions: Mix together well.
Let flavors blend for one hour.
Serve chilled with crackers or chips.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Ritz crackers.
Cook until bubbles.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Brown 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook carrots, drain and mash.
Combine all ingredients including mashed carrots in blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Grease a 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour mixture into dish. Sprinkle the top with cinnamon and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: ham roll-up
directions: Mix cream cheese, seasoning, garlic powder and onions.
Spread on ham like mayonnaise.
Roll and refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut in small sections to serve.

title: pudding pie
directions: Beat whipped topping mix with 1 cup milk and the vanilla, using large mixer bowl; beat at high with electric mixer about 6 minutes or until topping thickens and forms peaks.
Add remaining milk and the pie filling mix; blend at low.
Beat at high for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pie shell. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: barbecue hash
directions: Simmer about 1 hour.

title: chicken marimba
directions: Cook noodles in large amount of water until tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: date cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over medium heat 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and add nuts and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients. Drop spoonful on pan and make hole in center with thumb.
Put spoonful of date mixture in hole and bring up sides. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: ireenies beanies
directions: Brown beef; drain and put in crock-pot.
Brown bacon with onion; drain and put in crock-pot with remaining ingredients. Stir; cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls. Refrigerate.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place peaches on top of batter. Cream the cream cheese with peach juice and 1 cup sugar and pour over peaches.
Sprinkle cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Completely cover each egg with sausage meat.
Roll first in flour, then egg, then butter crumbs.
Shake off surplus crumbs. Deep-fry to a golden brown in moderately hot fat.
Drain well. Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken holiday wreath(by pampered chef)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop pepper, broccoli and onion. Separate chicken.
Combine all ingredients except rolls.
Unroll rolls and arrange triangles in a circle on a baking stone with bases overlapping in center and points toward the outside (similar to a sun's rays).
Scoop filling mixture onto widest portion of each roll triangle.
Fold points of triangles over filling and tuck under base at center (making a wreath).

title: bakeless fruit cake
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Make out into 2 rolls using wax paper.
Refrigerate and slice in 1/4 inch slices. The longer this sets the better it gets.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine soup with sour cream.
Fold in onions, carrots and squash.
Combine croutons and melted butter.
Spread 1/2 mix
on bottom and put vegetables on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chinatown chuck roast(cooking on the outdoor grill)
directions: Prepare marinade.
Marinate roast overnight, turning frequently.
Charcoal for 15 minutes on each side for medium rare, depending on thickness.
Thinly slice diagonally.

title: oven stew
directions: Cover and bake 5 hours at 250°.

title: german cutout cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in food processor or with mixer at medium speed until smooth.
Gradually mix in flour and salt. Chill 1 hour.
On a floured surface roll out dough 1/3 at a time to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes, place on cookie sheet and decorate as desired.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and cool on rack.
Makes about 7 dozen 2 inch cookies.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat yolks to cream; add juice, rind and milk to first 3 ingredients.
Last, fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm in center.

title: butcha coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and flour. Mix into a stiff dough.
Let rise.
Knead down and let rise again.
Then roll out and put in two 9 x 13-inch pans. Let rise again.
Spread 1 cup sour cream on top of each pan. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on each pan to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese and jelly cookies(low-fat and sugar-free)
directions: Mix the butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix in the flour, Equal and salt.
Refrigerate about 3 hours.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface.
Cut into rounds with 3 inch cutter. Place 1/4 teaspoon fruit in center.
Fold in half and crimp edges with fork.
Put slit on top.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: texas trash(t.v. snacks)
directions: Melt oil and oleo.
Add spices and sauces.
Mix well and cook together a few minutes.
Pour over cereals, nuts and pretzel mixture.
Bake in a 200° oven, stirring every 15 minutes, for 1 hour.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix and pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
When half done, add 4 tablespoons grated cheese to buttered bread crumbs.
Put on top of corn and finish baking.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients and add eggs and milk; beating until smooth.
Heat 1/4-inch oil at 375° in a skillet.
Cover bottom opening of a funnel with finger (funnel opening of at least 3/8-inch works best).

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla to mixture.
Mix flour and salt.
Blend the two mixtures and chill for 20 minutes.
Roll out and cut cookies. Bake 15 minutes.

title: golden fruit punch(serving size: 50)
directions: Combine juices and sugar.
Pour in gallon jug and freeze. Remove from freezer for 5 hours before serving.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Makes 50 one-half cup servings.

title: american lasagne
directions: Combine
beaten
eggs with 2 teaspoons salt and pepper; set aside.
Brown
meat
slowly;
spoon
off excess fat.
Add garlic, basil,
oregano,
sugar, parsley flakes, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Combine cottage
cheese
with
beaten eggs.
Place half noodles in buttered 13 x
9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread half cottage cheese mixture over
noodles.
Add
half cheese (Mozzarella or Swiss), save other half for
top.
Add
half
of meat mixture. Repeat layer.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make into marble sized balls and bake approximately 10 minutes at 275°.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Simmer sausage in 3 cups water for 20 minutes.
Add other ingredients and simmer at least an hour.
Yields 12 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes (5 minutes on High in microwave).
Best if kept warm while serving.
Serve with little bread rounds or crackers.

title: microwave toffee
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in a 9-inch circle on a greased cookie sheet; set aside.
Coat the top 2 inches of a 2 1/2-quart glass bowl with butter.
Place remaining butter in bowl.
Add sugar, salt and water; do not stir.
Microwave at High for 11 minutes or until mixture just begins to turn light brown.
Pour over pecans. Sprinkle morsels over mixture and let stand 1 minute, then sprinkle with 1/4 cup finely chopped pecans.
Chill and break into pieces.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Coat
chicken
in
combined flour and
seasonings.
Dip chicken in egg and water;
coat with crumbs and cheese.
Place in 13	x
9-inch
baking pan.	Drizzle margarine over chicken. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: raisin rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Place in a pan of water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Stir the baking soda into the flour.
Stir the vanilla into the milk.
Then add milk to flour mixture gradually.
Put into muffin tins and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Ty's favorite.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add dried shrimp (blotted on paper towels), crumbling into cheese and cream mixture.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Stir until combined well.
Cover and let rest in fridge for at least 1/2 hour.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: turkey mornay
directions: In a skillet cook and drain bacon; set aside.
Add mushrooms and onions to skillet.
Saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, thyme and pepper.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Add broth and milk, stirring.
Bring to a boil.
Boil until thick.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Simmer 4 minutes.
In large bowl place bacon, sauce, macaroni, asparagus, turkey and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Toss lightly.
Spoon mixture in lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Flavor improves with standing.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil together, stirring constantly, for one minute the sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Remove from heat and stir in, mixing until smooth, the peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over the oatmeal, stirring until all oatmeal is covered.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set 1/2 hour or until cool.

title: meat loaf he loves
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce, using hands.
Form into loaf shape, in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off fat.
Pour can of tomato sauce on top.
Bake additional 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: prune tarts
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is size of little peas.
Mix together eggs and sour cream; add to dry ingredients.
Dough will be stiff.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.
Roll out on a floured surface. Cut with a tart cutter.
Place 1 teaspoon of prune mixture in center of tart.
Cross strips of dough over the center to form a pinwheel or star shaped tart.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy orange pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Spoon in ice cream, stirring until melted and smooth.
Chill until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Pour gelatin mixture into crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together and form ball. Serve with crackers.

title: peach fruit dip
directions: In blender combine first four ingredients. Cover and blend until smooth. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: tasty whipped squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove seeds.
Place cut side down in shallow baking pans; add 1/2-inch water.
Cover and bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until tender.
Drain; scoop out pulp and discard shell.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9 inch metal pan.
Place marshmallows in bottom of pan.
Combine strawberries and gelatin and pour over marshmallows. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over gelatin mixture. Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Follow directions on box, substituting milk for water.
Make two layers and split layers with thread.
Put together with filling while cake is warm.

title: oven roasted corn
directions: Place ears of corn in husks in a moderate oven (350°) and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove husks and silk and serve hot with butter. Oven roasted corn has the flavor of corn served at corn roasts or clambakes.

title: parmesan spirals* * * * *
directions: As near as I can figure out, we were in France in the fifties when this recipe came into my possession, but I don't recall who gave it to me or where it came from.
Living in a trailer with a husband and five children didn't help to keep things organized except to put them in a box under the bed.
As time went on, the bed became higher and higher.

title: cranberry orange crush
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale; bring to a boil. Cook for 5 minutes.
Strain juice and chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serve over ice in cups or in a punch bowl. Yields 110 (4-ounce) cups.

title: fat free carrot muffins
directions: About 1 hour before serving, preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8 large muffin pan cups with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, soda, baking powder and ginger.
In large bowl with wire whisk or fork, mix shredded carrots, yogurt, egg substitute, applesauce, raisins, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
With spoon, stir flour mixture into carrot mixture just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of each muffin comes out clean.
Cool muffins in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes; remove muffins from pan.
Cool slightly on wire rack. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: summer spaghetti(delicious all year round!)
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake, covered, 15 minutes in preheated 425° oven.
Drain fat.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch and oregano.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Pour heated sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Put cranberries and oranges (including the rind) through the food grinder (coarse blade). Stir in sugar and chill.
Makes 2 pints.
Keeps well for weeks stored in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook 2 cups strawberries, sugar, water, food coloring and cornstarch together until clear and thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Pour into graham cracker crust and cool.
Top with whipped cream and reserved strawberries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: marinated collard greens
directions: Steam greens until tender in salted water.
Drain thoroughly. Sprinkle ingredients on top of them.
Toss.
Marinate a few hours in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: company chicken breasts
directions: Flour, salt and pepper chicken; brown in oil.
Place browned chicken in baking dish.
Pour off excess oil.
Brown flour in skillet.
Add broth.
Season gravy with salt and pepper to taste. Add mushrooms.
Pour gravy over chicken and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with rice.
May be prepared a day early or frozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add corn and muffin mix. Gently mix with fork.
Add eggs and mix gently. Stir in cheese. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and then refrigerate.

title: stewed tomato salad
directions: Heat stewed tomatoes to boiling.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add salt and vinegar.
Pour into suitable mold and chill until congealed.

title: special goodie bars
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar and bring to boil.
Add peanut butter and margarine; blend well.
Put cereal in large bowl and pour hot mixture over; stir until well coated.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with chocolate chips.
Put under broiler until chips spread easily.
Chill and cut into bars.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix and enjoy. Very good.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg, molasses and vinegar.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Flatten as thin as you can.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly and remove to rack.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, salt and pepper. Make into beef patties. Coat the patties in flour. Fry patties in a small amount of shortening until golden brown. Place in baking dish. Combine soup and water; pour this mixture over patties and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: 20 minute tamale pie
directions: Heat butter in 10 to 12-inch skillet with cover.
Add onion and meat and cook until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, corn with liquid, sour cream, corn meal and seasonings.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: After removing all dust, wipe screen doors with kerosene and they will look new.
As long as the odor remains, mosquitoes and moth millers will give them a wide berth.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion and margarine.
Mix all together and place in covered dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add chopped cucumber (skin off) and chopped tomatoes.
Mix in shredded Mozzarella, dry Zesty Italian packet and bottled dressing.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 10 to 20.
Cut in half for smaller portion.

title: sausage and corn casserole
directions: Boil sausage in water until water has evaporated, about 15 minutes.
Brown 5 minutes.
Remove and drain off fat.
