Reserve 2 tablespoons fat.
Saute onion and green pepper in fat until onion is transparent.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add corn and tomatoes and cook until liquid is evaporated, about 20 minutes.
Arrange sausage on top and heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain well and save liquor.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring, until blended and smooth, but not brown.
Add onion; cook slowly until soft.
Add liquid slowly, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Add cheese (cut in small pieces) and seasonings.
Stir until cheese melts.
Combine with cooked spinach.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: no mess cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 cake pan. Pour pineapple in pan; pour dry cake mix evenly over pineapple. Pour nuts and coconut evenly over cake mix; pour melted oleo evenly over top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and egg yolks together.
Add flour and stir well.
Then, add milk, vanilla and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.

title: sourdough starter
directions: In a crock or similar container with lots of room for expansion, dissolve yeast in water, then add sugar.
Stir in flour and molasses using a wooden spoon until smooth paste.
Cover loosely and let stand at room temperature to 80° for 3 to 5 days. Stir starter down and repeat once a day while fermenting 3 weeks. Use when making bread.

title: red chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Combine three ingredients. Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Cover and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Line aluminum foil on a cookie sheet.
Arrange crackers to cover cookie sheet.
Melt sugar and butter.
Let boil 3 minutes. Pour over crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes in preheated oven at 400°. Spread chocolate chips over crackers.
Cover with walnuts and refrigerate until cool.
Break into pieces.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Boil together all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Cool and pour over slaw, tossing well.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix all other ingredients and lay chops on top of rice.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn dogs
directions: Cook in deep fat at 400° until brown (about 3 minutes).
Makes about 20.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: In large dish, combine Jell-O and boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice.
Fold into Jell-O mix the pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Put half of mixture in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate until firm, 1 1/2 hours or so. Evenly spread sour cream over top.
Gently spoon on rest of strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve on lettuce.

title: old fashioned homemade dumplings and chicken
directions: Cover hen with water in large kettle; salt to taste.
Boil until meat is tender.
Keep adding boiling water so there will be about 3 quarts of broth when tender.
Taste broth to be sure it has a real chicken flavor.
If it doesn't, boil more and have less broth.
When broth is ready beat together in large bowl the following:
condensed milk and eggs.
Sift together in separate bowl, flour, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to milk and eggs mixture, gradually blending until it makes a stiff dough.
Knead until dough is not too sticky and is handled easily.
Roll out on floured board as thin as possible.
Cut into strips and small pieces.
Drop one at a time until you have desired amount.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in blender and serve.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Take off skins.
Heat sugar, vinegar, beet juice and a little cinnamon, cloves or allspice to a boil.
Add beets.
Let come to a boil and put in sterilized jars. Seal or may keep in refrigerator.

title: layered jello
directions: You will need a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Takes about 4 hours to complete.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and garnish.

title: strawberry marshmallow dessert
directions: Melt milk and marshmallows over low heat.
Cool.
Fold in 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip.
Fold in 1 box of thawed strawberries. Refrigerate until ready to serve, then spoon into Nut Crust.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash, slice and steam cook squash until tender.
Put squash and onion into Pyrex baking dish.
Chop cooked squash into smaller pieces.
Drain off liquid.
Add butter and all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Sprinkle a little extra cheese and dressing crumbs on top and dot with a little butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until golden and bubbly.

title: apple pie
directions: Arrange apple slices in pastry shell; sprinkle with 1 cup sugar, salt, cinnamon, 5 teaspoons flour and water.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour and margarine in a bowl; mix until a crumbly texture is achieved.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on pie.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown onion, beef and sausage.
Put in crock-pot with cheese and tomatoes.
Cook until cheese is melted. Stir occasionally. Serve with nacho chips.

title: beef and mushroom quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Saute onions, mushrooms and green peppers until tender.
Add beef; brown.
In large bowl, blend eggs, mayonnaise, milk, cheese and flour.
Stir in meat mixture.
Pour mixture evenly in crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: party mix snack
directions: Mix all Chex and pretzels together in a large baking pan.
Mix together in a saucepan the rest of the ingredients and heat until the butter is melted.
Pour over the mixture in the baking pan; mix thoroughly.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes or longer until all are heated through.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: maple walnut cream
directions: In the top of a double boiler over boiling water, scald syrup and 1 3/4 cups milk.
Combine cornstarch, salt and remaining milk. Gradually add to the syrup mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 25 minutes.
Add a small amount to eggs.
Return all to pan and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour into serving dishes and sprinkle with walnuts.
Cool.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chili casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a large casserole.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking.
Bake in 350° oven (macaroni doesn't need to be cooked).

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook and stir onion and garlic in butter and oil for one minute. Add shrimp. Cook and stir until shrimp are pink. Add lemon juice and salt. Heat through.

title: garlic toast
directions: Preheat oven 400°.
Mix all ingredients together. Evenly spread bread slices with the mixed ingredients.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake 8 minutes in a 400° oven.
Turn to broil and lightly brown, watching carefully not to burn.
The bread will smell too strong, but it doesn't taste that way at all.
Remember, the smell of garlic is only a problem for the ones who do not partake!
Serves 4

title: nanny's congo bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in brown sugar until mixed, then set aside to cool slightly.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour mixture; stir well.
Mix in chocolate chips (and nuts if using them).
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake!
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: cream tortillas
directions: In saucepan, combine peppers to taste and onions.
Add 1/4 cup water and cook for 10 minutes.
Add chicken and mushroom soup. Heat until blended.
Add grated cheese and broken tortillas.
Save enough cheese to crumble and sprinkle on top.
Place in casserole dish and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Spray Pam in a deep casserole dish.
Layer ingredients in order listed; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Brown croutons in butter and top casserole when ready to serve.

title: hot fudge cream puffs
directions: In a medium saucepan, crumble pie crust.
Mix into boiling water; cook and stir vigorously until pastry forms a ball and leaves the side of pan.
Remove from heat.
Cool for 10 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating with a wooden spoon after each addition until smooth.
For each cream puff, spoon about 1/4 cup of the mixture onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffs are dry and golden brown. Remove from baking sheet; cool on wire racks.
Cut off tops; remove excess webbing.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well, adding eggs, one at a time. Fill individual aluminum baking cups with 2 full tablespoons of mixture.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and put a tablespoon of mixture on top of each cake. Bake at 300° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 30 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all up.
Pour in pie crust; add other crust over top. Cook for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Stir in cracker crumbs, pecans, coconut, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Roll in walnut-sized balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin.
Dip balls in mixture and put on waxed paper to cool.

title: pasta phylimena
directions: Combine chopped basil, oregano, green onions and tomato with pressed garlic, vinegar and olive oil.
Add mixture to cooked pasta (your favorite kind).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Ready to serve or chill for 1/2 hour.

title: oatmeal butterscotch cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and baking soda. In a large mixing bowl, combine butter, sugars and pudding mix. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in oats and butterscotch morsels. Batter will be stiff. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam vegetable spray.
Put bread in bottom of dish.
Mix eggs, milk and soup together.
Top bread with sausage.
Pour mixture over; put 1 cup grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden on top.

title: impossible chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate.
Sprinkle chicken, mushrooms, salt and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake uncovered until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: vanilla wafer pound cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients, then add last 2.
Grease and flour pan good.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: mexican skillet dinner
directions: Brown sausage in a deep heavy skillet; add onions and green pepper.
Cook until onions are golden brown.
Pour off excess fat. Add remaining ingredients; stir to moisten macaroni.
Cover; bring to a boil, then reduce heat and cook 30 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Toss melted butter and crumbs; set aside.
Cook squash in water until tender.
Put in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix together mayonnaise, egg, cheese, margarine, sugar and onion. Pour over squash, mixing well.
Add crumbs topping.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in oven at 325°, uncovered, for one hour.

title: olive craver's light refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften lard in hot water.
Add sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add egg; mix altogether well.
Add flour and beat well.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Dough will be soft until it chills.
Make out into rolls 1 hour before baking to double the dough.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
May be kept in refrigerator for 2 or 3 weeks.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Mix cake according to package.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, slightly greased.
Beat eggs, sugar and Ricotta.
Pour egg mixture by tablespoon into batter.
Cut through batter back and forth with knife.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from lima, kidney and Great Northern beans. Combine sugar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt, cheese and onion.
Mix with beans.
Bake for 1 hour in a buttered 2-quart casserole at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil the hens in a large quantity of water with the onions, peppers and celery until chicken is ready to pull off bone. Remove hens from the stock.
Bone and cut into bite-size pieces. Set aside.
Strain stock and boil spaghetti in stock until done. Pour off excess stock and reserve.
Add chicken to spaghetti.
Add tomato sauce, mushroom soup and grated cheese.
Mix well and simmer on top of range for an hour.
It it gets too thick, add some of the stock which has been reserved.
This tastes as good the second day as the first.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in water and drain.
Beat eggs; add soup, mayonnaise, chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Add broccoli and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt butter and add stuffing mix; put in casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: basic crepe mixture
directions: Put the liquids, eggs and salt into the blender.
Add the flour, then the butter.
Cover and blend at top speed for 1 minute.
If bits of flour adhere to sides of jar, dislodge with a spoon and blend with spoon for 1 to 3 seconds more.
Cover and let stand for at least 2 hours.

title: white marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine the cream and sugar and cook until it forms soft ball (closer to hard ball).
Pour over remaining ingredients, which have been combined in a mixing bowl.
Mix well and pour into a buttered pan or dish.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion until cooked.
Pour in can of sauce.
Boil water. Cook noodles. Combine all ingredients except cheese into casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Sprinkle cheese (as much as desired) on top. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Good.

title: hot rolls
directions: Use a large bowl.
Put yeast in bowl; mix in sugar, eggs, salt, warm water, oil and flour.
Knead well; cover and set aside for 8 hours or overnight.
For individual muffins, make roll about size of golf ball.
For plain rolls, put golf ball size rolls all into same pan.
Let rise.
Bake for 12 minutes at 375°, until golden brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Add beaten eggs and oil. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Chill.
Roll into small balls.
Press with bottom of glass dipped into sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 8 dozen.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil; add rice, mushrooms, onion and soy sauce.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add meat and egg.
Stir and cook 5 minutes over low heat.
May substitute ham, shrimp, lean beef strips, etc.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soups, broth and Veg-All.
Pour over cooked chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Press biscuits into a pie pan, forming a crust.
Melt together butter and sugar.
Add cream cheese and melt (this will not melt completely).
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pour mixture into crust and bake at 350° until done (per biscuit wrapper).

title: play dough
directions: Take twelve fine, full-grown months.
See that these are thoroughly free from all old memories of bitterness, rancor, hate and jealousy.
Cleanse them completely from every clinging spite. Pick off all specks of pettiness and littleness.
In short, see that these months are free from all the past.
Have them as fresh and clean as when they first came from the great storehouse of time.
Cut each month into thirty or thirty-one equal parts.
This batch will keep for just one year.
Do not attempt to make up the whole batch at one time, as so many persons spoil it in doing so.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash and core apples.
In large saucepan, put sugar, water and corn syrup.
Mix well and add apples.
Cover and cook over low heat until apples are tender.
Turn apples over so both sides will be done.

title: apple butter
directions: Boil the cider until reduced to 1 quart.
Pare the apples and slice thinly.
Put the apples into cider and cook very slowly, stirring frequently, until it begins to thicken.
Add sugar, syrup and cinnamon and continue to cook until thick enough to spread when cool.
Seal in sterilized jars.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: chicken pie
directions: Make pastry and cut 1/2-inch bigger than casserole.
Place chicken and vegetables in a dish.
Make sauce by melting butter; add flour.
Blend thoroughly, slowly add chicken stock, salt and pepper; stir well until mixed and thick.
Pour over vegetables and chicken.
Cover with pastry.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: not your mother's green beans
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Stir in pine nuts.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Cut chicken into smaller pieces and add to chicken broth in large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add beans, corn, salsa, two cups broken tortilla chips and seasonings.
Heat mixture thoroughly. Ladle into soup bowls and garnish with cheese and remaining tortilla chips.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spanish casserole(serves 10)
directions: Brown onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add ground chuck.
Drain off grease.
Add tomato puree and hot sauce.
Cook down a bit.
In a bowl mix cold chili and seasoning into a smooth paste.
Add to meat mixture.
Cook down until slightly thick.
Cut tortillas in 1/4ths.
Line baking casserole.
Add a layer of sauce. Alternate and end with sauce.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 seconds.
Keeps well.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Peel zucchini.
Cut into small cubes, discarding seeds.
In a saucepan, put zucchini, onion, bouillon cubes and 1 cup water. Cook until zucchini and onion are soft.
Drain.
Soften cream cheese and butter or margarine in microwave.
Beat 3 eggs; add cream cheese and butter and beat again.
Mix in zucchini and onion.
Pour in 2-quart casserole and top with buttered croutons. Bake as you would a pumpkin pie at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: *Add enough water to the pineapple and blueberry juices to make 2 cups.

title: mistake apricot cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients until well blended (thinning with a small amount of milk, if necessary) to spreading or drizzling consistency.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Brown almonds and chicken.
Mix sherry or wine vinegar with next 4 ingredients and add to chicken.
Cook until thickened.
Add pea pods.
Serve over rice.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain off excess grease. Add beans, seasoning and juice. Cook on medium heat 30 minutes or more.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Pare potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch sticks.
Place on heavy-duty foil.
Sprinkle with desired amounts of seasonings and generous amount of Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Seal foil securely, allowing room for expansion of steam.
Grill over medium heat on preheated gas grill about 45 to 50 minutes or until done, turn several times.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken thoroughly and debone, if necessary.
Melt margarine in skillet. Add celery and onion and cook until tender. Stir in next 5 ingredients; blend well. Add cubed chicken, almonds and mushrooms.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: holiday cider
directions: Pour cider or juice and red hots in large pan on stove. Bring to boil, stirring occasionally until red hots are melted. Remove from heat and serve in a clear glass punch bowl for a festive look.
Serve warm.
Reheat as needed.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: To cut fat, use skim milk, Egg Beaters and low-fat cheese.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and mix.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: copper pennies
directions: Bring peppers, onions, soup, sugar, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce to a boil. Simmer until sugar is dissolved (1 or 2 minutes). Pour over cooked carrots. Serve hot or cold. Great for picnics or buffets. Keeps well.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Sift into creamed mixture alternately with the mashed bananas beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Set paper baking cups into muffin tins and fill 2/3 full with the banana muffin batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until muffins are golden brown on top and springy to the touch.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour over butter.
Add 1 large can peaches with juice.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tea time scones
directions: Combine dry ingredients. With pastry blender or two knives, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. In separate bowl, combine egg, buttermilk, and vanilla. Using fork, stir into dry ingredients to form a soft dough. Gather into a ball. Knead lightly (10 times) on floured surface. Pat dough 1/2-inch thick. Cut as you would cut a pie; do not separate pieces.

title: san francisco salad
directions: Simmer the first 5 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Cool; combine with beef and onion and chill several hours.
Drain, saving marinade.
Break up lettuce and place in a large bowl.
Top with beef and onion.
Combine sour cream and reserved marinade.
Toss with lettuce and beef.
Garnish with artichoke hearts and tomato wedges.
Serves 6.

title: oven barbecued brisketlincoln, nebraska
directions: Pour liquid smoke over brisket in a baking dish.
Generously sprinkle meal on both sides with celery powder, garlic powder and onion powder.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Stir in milk and shortening. Blend in nuts.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over entire batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
During baking the cake mixture rises to the top and chocolate sauce settles to the bottom.
Invert squares of pudding on dessert plates.
Dip sauce from pan over each piece.
Best served warm, but is good cold too. Can put Cool Whip on top.
Easy and inexpensive.

title: chicken livers with mushrooms
directions: Cook together for 5 minutes one slice bacon cut in pieces and butter.
Remove the bacon bits.
Add chopped onion and cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken livers, cook 2 minutes.
Add flour, bouillon, lemon juice and mushrooms; cook 2 minutes more. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at
a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, mixing
well.
Stir
in
lemon juice and lemon extract.
Pour
batter
into
greased
and
well-floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350°
for
1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted
into center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix all four ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Freeze.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend butter and oleo.
Add cheeses and put in refrigerator to harden.
Roll in 2 balls or 1 large ball.
Roll in nuts.
May be frozen.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Shred the first 4 ingredients.
Bring sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric powder, salt and pepper to boil.
Mix together with cabbage, peppers and onions.
Let stand for 8 hours before eating.

title: skillet chicken paella
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Cook in 10-inch skillet in hot oil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Cook garlic and onion until tender, but not brown.
Remove pan from heat.
Add broth, uncooked rice, oregano, paprika, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, bell pepper and frozen peas.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in cooked chicken and cook 1 minute or more.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix sugars with margarine.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: bbq ribs
directions: Boil ribs for about 15 minutes. Place ribs in baking dish and add salt and pepper to taste. Cover with BBQ sauce. Bake on 400 degrees until done.

title: taco spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat in large skillet.
Drain and add salt, tomato sauce, water and taco seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil and add spaghetti.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir often.

title: beef stew
directions: Coat cut up round steak with flour and fry in oil with minced onion.
Remove meat after brown and stir in brown gravy mix and blend with oil.
Add beef consomme soup and water until right gravy consistency.
Add meat again, raw potatoes and carrots and cook on low heat until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits.
Add margarine, cheese, milk and eggs, beaten. Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: orange refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Dissolve jello in
3/4	cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Set aside.	Mix and bake cake as directed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch
pan.
Cool	20
to	25 minutes.
Poke deep holes about 1 inch apart in cake,
still	in
pan, with a meat fork. Pour
jello mixture
into
holes.
Refrigerate
cake
while preparing topping.
In
a
chilled bowl blend and whip topping mix, instant pudding, cold milk and vanilla until stiff, 3 to 8 minutes. Immediately
frost cake and store in refrigerator. Serve chilled.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil; then add chocolate chips and mix until smooth.
Delicious on ice cream!

title: danish puff
directions: Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water and mix with a fork.
Round into a ball and divide dough in half.
Pat dough with hands into 2 long strips 12 x 4-inches.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.

title: salmon with lemon basil sauce
directions: Combine minced shallots, minced garlic, lemon juice, Tabasco sauce, dry mustard, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and white vinegar.
Simmer at a gentle boil over medium heat until mixture is reduced by about 1/3.
Add unsalted butter, lemon peels and basil.
Heat until butter is melted.

title: cherry valentine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool slightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients; pour into oiled mold.
Refrigerate until set.
When ready to serve, unmold onto salad greens.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Bring into a boil 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup water.
Add 1 cup flour. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each one. Spread over a greased cookie sheet with sides. Bake 15 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together.
Melt chocolate with butter.
Stir chocolate mixture with dry ingredients, along with milk and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan.

title: lemon-lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the hot water thoroughly; add the softened cream cheese and beat with a mixer.
Mix the milk and mayonnaise together and stir in.
Add the pineapple and nuts; stir until mixed.
Cover with a plastic wrap and refrigerate until set.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Discard all but 3 cups of liquid. Add all of the ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender. Serve over white rice.

title: rum cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks in mixer until light and add sugar.
Soak gelatin in cold water; put over low fire and bring to boil (more water might be needed), stirring.
Whip cream until stiff; fold it into the egg mixture and flavor with rum.
Pour into oiled mold and chill.
Will keep for days and days.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and beat well.
Pour this over first layer and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: no-name dessert
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with squares of angel food cake.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and juice, plus enough water to make 2 cups.
Pour over cake and refrigerate 1 hour.
Arrange peaches and sliced bananas on top.
Beat pudding with milk for 2 minutes.
Spread on top of fruit.
Drain pineapple and spread over pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: quick doughnuts
directions: Bring one-half inch cooking oil in frying pan to medium heat. Take center out with Pepsi bottle.
Add 1/2 doughnuts and cook until brown, approximately 1 minute, then turn.
Dip in mixture of sugars and cinnamon when cooled.

title: pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops.
Put flour on plate.
Mix eggs in bowl. Place bread crumbs on plate.
Coat pork chops in flour, dip in eggs, then coat in bread crumbs.
Place oil in frying pan, heat and follow with pork chop.
Turn 1 time.

title: coffee layers
directions: Boil 3/4 cups of water and add 1-1/2 Tbsp. coffee powder and 2 tsp. sugar.
Continue boiling for another 30 seconds and remove from heat.
Let cool.
When completely cooled, add whipped topping and mix well.
Keep aside.

title: cheese garlic biscuits(just like red lobster)
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.
Serve warm.

title: spiced percolator punch
directions: Pour liquids into 8-cup percolator.
Put remaining ingredients in basket.
Perk.
Yields 1 quart.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Mix cookies and margarine together.
Save some for topping and put remainder in a 9 x 13 inch pan and refrigerate.
Beat cream cheese and confectionary sugar and add 1/2 of the Cool Whip. Pour over crust and refrigerate again.
Mix instant pudding and milk together and beat for 2 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: dill pickled tomatoes
directions: Pack tomatoes into hot sterile jars.
To each quart, add the amounts listed of alum, garlic and dill.
Combine vinegar, salt and water; bring to boil.
Fill jars with liquid and seal.
One jalapeno pepper may be added to each jar if desired.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck with chopped onion.
Drain and rinse off. Cover bottom of pan with spray.
Then place chopped cabbage in bottom of pan.
Salt and pepper cabbage.
Top with browned ground chuck and onions.
Add another layer of cabbage.
Top with can of tomato soup mixed with 1/2 cup of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Great with mashed potatoes.

title: mom's barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Drain off any grease. Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: chocolate mousse torte
directions: Prepare brownies as directed.
Make chocolate mousse pie as directed; refrigerate.
Cool brownies, insert holes and baste Amaretto liqueur.
Cut brownies and place 1/2 on bottom of large glass bowl.
Add 1/2 of mousse pie; break 3 Heath candy bars on top.
Layer 1/2 carton cream whip.
Repeat layers, ending with whip cream.
Top with slivers of chocolate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in bowl and beat until creamy; add vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and tartar together and add slowly to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in bowl.
Bring to a boil the oleo, water and peanut butter; pour over dry mixture.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar into cream cheese.
Add crushed pineapple.
Add slightly thawed strawberries.
Add firm bananas, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish; freeze. Thaw very slightly to serve.
Serves 10 or more.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add
sugar
gradually
and
mix well. Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir
in
soda,	salt,
flour and oats. Form small balls and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.	Makes 5 dozen.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix well and use the blender.
This is enough for 2 to 3 batches of cole slaw.
Keeps well in the fridge.

title: easy cucumber pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let stand 3 hours at room temperature.
Drain.
In a large pan, combine remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer 5 minutes. Add cucumbers and onions.
Heat again until mixture starts to boil. Pack in hot sterilized jars.
Seal and store in refrigerator until needed.

title: christmas bazaar cranberry relish
directions: This recipe requires a food processor.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt butter or oleo.
Dip each biscuit in butter until completely coated, then dip biscuits in brown sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place each biscuit in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 475°.
Dribble 10x icing over each biscuit, if desired.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar, flour, meal and butter; add beaten eggs.
Beat and add milk, salt, coconut and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 475° until it begins to brown and then reduce heat to 300° until set.
(Add pecans if desired.)

title: beer-basa soup au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wrap kielbasa in foil and bake 30 minutes.
When cool, remove casing and dice; set aside.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add onions and garlic; saute until tender. Add broth, beer, rye bread cubes, thyme and kielbasa.
Heat to boiling and remove from heat.

title: fresh garden salad
directions: Prepare Creamettes macaroni according to package; drain. Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill 6 to 8 servings.

title: chewy treats
directions: Mix white syrup and sugar in saucepan. Let boil for 1 minute. Take off of heat. Mix in peanut butter and cocoa crisps. Place on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: apricot delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then add cold water.
Mix well.
Add pineapple.
Drain and keep juice.
Add bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: auntie bee's sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Gradually add combined dry ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Roll dough 1/3 at a time, on lightly floured surface, to 3/8-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets; sprinkle with sugar, if desired, or leave off sugar and frost.

title: peanut bran bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in heavy saucepan over low heat. Stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Combine last 4 ingredients in well-greased pan.
Pour syrup over top.
Let cool and cut into 40 bars.
Equals 1 starch and 1 fat exchange.

title: tabouli
directions: Place burgul in a soup or cereal bowl.
Pour water in bowl until burgul is just covered.
Let sit.
Chop parsley leaves very fine (discard stems).
Chop mint, tomatoes and onion very fine. Put parsley and mint in large bowl and fill with water to wash leaves.
Drain water and squeeze parsley and mint as dry as possible.
Drain burgul of excess water.
Combine parsley, mint, tomatoes, onion and burgul.
Mix lemon juice and oil.
Add to parsley mixture.
Add salt to taste.
Let stand at least 1/2 hour. Adjust lemon juice, oil and salt to taste.
Should be able to taste just a shade more lemon juice than oil.
Traditionally eaten by putting tabouli in romaine lettuce leaves.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Separate eggs (2 bowls).
Put cream of tartar in egg whites. In large bowl with egg yolks, beat in all other ingredients.
Beat egg whites until dry and fluffy.
Slowly mix whites with other ingredients.
Bake in ungreased large tube pan at 350° for 1 hour. Cool cake by inverting pan (I use long neck bottle).

title: sweet & sour pork(chicken, shrimp, etc....)
directions: Brown pork slowly in hot shortening:
add 1 cup water, bouillon cube and 1/4 teaspoon salt; mix well.
Cover and simmer until tender (approx. 1 hr.).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients except last two (cornflakes and butter).
Mix together cornflakes and butter.
Put mixture in casserole dish.
Top with cornflake mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: yogurt milkshake
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender.
Serve.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Blend sour cream, soup and 1/4 cup butter.
Alternate layers of potatoes, onions, cheese, salt and sauce in a buttered dish. Top with cornflakes.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Ummm good!!!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; save broth and debone.
Place chicken pieces in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together soup and milk.
Beat until smooth and pour over chicken.
Cover with bread crumbs and moisten thoroughly with broth.
(May look too moist but it's not.)
Let set for a couple of hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put the Minute rice in a baking dish with just a little butter.
Mix the soups and milk; pour over rice.
Put pieces of uncooked chicken on top (no salt).
Pour the onion soup mix over it.
Cover it with foil; bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour three 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans. Stir together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside. Stir together pumpkin, oil, water and eggs in large bowl; gradually add dry ingredients, stirring until well blended. Stir in peanut butter chips, nuts and raisins, if desired. Pour evenly into prepared pans. Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pans to wire rack. Cool completely.

title: heavenly hash mounds
directions: Melt chocolate with syrup and water on low heat.
Remove from heat and add nuts and marshmallows.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator.

title: caitee's favorite chicken wings(appetizer or main meat dish)
directions: Wash chicken wings and place in a single layer in a large roasting pan.
Heat remaining ingredients in a saucepan over low heat until butter is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Pour this mixture evenly over chicken wings and put into a preheated 325° oven.
Bake at this temperature for approximately 30 to 40 minutes, turning wings each 15 minutes or so.
Increase oven temperature to 400° and bake for an additional 15 minutes or until wings look "glossy".
Make sure to turn wings at least one time during this last 15 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan immediately. (It is also a very good idea to include "finger bowls" with these since your paper napkins have a tendency to "stick" to your fingers.)

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in drippings.
Add hamburger, mushrooms, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, and seasonings, mix well.
Alternate layers of spaghetti, sauce, pepperoni, and cheese in casserole (11 x 13).
Bake at 350° for 20 - 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: stephenson's bran muffins
directions: Soak cereals and raisins in milk for 5 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with cereal mixture.
Do not overmix.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: j. t.'s guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Serve with tortilla chips or as a condiment for Mexican dishes.

title: surprise meringues
directions: Beat egg
whites,
salt,
cream
of
tartar and vanilla until soft
peaks
form.
Add
sugar
gradually, beating until peaks hold
their
shape (don't underbeat).
Fold in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Cover cookie sheet with plain brown or white paper. Drop
mixture
by rounded teaspoonfuls onto the paper. Bake in slow
oven
(200° or 250°) about 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before removing from paper.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt, green pepper and onion together.
Brown sausage and drain.
Combine egg mixture and sausage and pour over bread.
(Break bread beforehand and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.) Spread cheese on top.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Measure ingredients after they have been sifted.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well. Add flour gradually and mix after each addition.
Add vanilla and blend.
Divide dough in half.
Shape into rolls approximately 1 3/4-inches in diameter.
Roll in waxed paper and chill overnight. Cut into thin slices.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 6 minutes or until well done.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pasta salad dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate to cool before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift and mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and stir well.
Add eggs and carrots.
Pour into greased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rorie's artichoke dip(hot)
directions: Note:
Spices to taste.
Can substitute garlic powder for minced garlic.

title: cheese and macaroni
directions: Boil macaroni and strain when cooked.
While macaroni is draining, place slices of cheese in bottom of pan and return to low heat until melted.
Stir in macaroni.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix.
Put in pan.

title: wheaties muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Blend in egg, milk, shortening and Wheaties.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pletzel(flat onion bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/4 cup warm water.
In a small saucepan, combine 1 cup water, 1 cup milk and oil.
Heat until warm, but do not boil.
Pour the milk into a large mixing bowl and mix with dissolved yeast.
Stir in salt and gradually stir in flour to make a soft, workable dough.
Remove to a lightly floured surface and knead for 10 minutes, until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place the dough in an oiled bowl; cover with a clean towel and let rise in a warm place until it has doubled in bulk, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Lightly grease 2 baking sheets with vegetable oil.
